title: May 13 NYS Safe Streets Coalition Lobby Day
description:
Join the New York Safe Streets Coalition May 13th Lobby Day! Families for Safe Streets, Transportation Alternatives, and other organizations from across New York City and New York State will be taking on Albany together and showing that we are a powerful force to contend with. But we need YOU to join us. This is our chance to talk directly with state legislators, tell them our stories, and make a real impact for safe streets. 

We have the tools to cure the traffic violence crisis, but we need bold action from our lawmakers, and we need you to deliver that message.

We will meet with elected officials to discuss the SAFE Streets package.
Learn more about the package at nyssafestreets.org.

RSVP now to secure your spot for what’s sure to be an inspiring day of action!

Transportation to Albany from NYC and Kingston is provided by bus. Train tickets may be provided as needed, for people with special needs. 
We will be doing trainings to prepare you for the lobby day on Friday, May 9th at 12pm and Monday, May 12th at 5:30pm.

title: Rush-hour Resistance Rally @ Melrose curve in Phoenix
description:
Big events with thousands of people are great. But we also need local, more frequent rallies that show locals that they're not alone in this fight. 

So I made one! 

Every Wednesday, @ 7am, we'll gather at Copper Star Coffee in midtown Phoenix to grab a beverage, walk down to the rainbow crosswalk across 7th Avenue, and show the busy morning commuters that they are not alone.

Peak traffic time seems to be from 7:30 to 8:30a. Yes, it's already hot in Phoenix, so plan accordingly. Bill from Copper Star has graciously (and excitedly!) offered to let us use the shop as a cooling off and bio-break place as needed.

Spread the word. Come join us. Or start your own!

All the details you need are at [RhRR.us](https://rhrr.us).

Love this idea and want to start your own Rush-hour Resistance Rally in your area? Groovy! Let's make that happen!

title: Four Corners in Lenexa  Standing Rally
description: As citizens, we can’t let the policies and actions of the Federal Government and unelected billionaires be normalized, but we can only stop what’s going on by coming together.  A STANDING RALLY  will draw attention to the situation, encouraging our neighbors to join with us. We will rally every Saturday morning from 11 AM – 12 PM.  Stay for the full hour or come by when and for how long you can. We will peacefully line the sidewalk on all four corners of 87th Parkway and Maurer Road,  holding signs on issues that are most meaningful to us or just simply standing in support of our neighbors and our country.  If sitting is more comfortable for you, you are very welcome to bring mobility or lawn chairs!! There is room for everyone!
accessibility_notes:
Here are a couple of notes on logistics.
Please be especially mindful of parking.  For example, if you live relatively nearby, please consider walking.  If you drive, there is street parking on the residential streets to the north and also a bit further on the south.  About ½ mile down on the west, there is a large civic campus garage at 17201 W 87th St. Pkwy.  In addition, on the SE, SW, and NW sides of the intersection, there are restaurants and shops with big, but commercially owned parking lots meant for customers.  (Please note that if you become a customer, it’s fine to bring snacks to the rally that you have bought, but please take any empty snack containers back home with you, when you leave. In any case, no matter which direction you are coming from, if it is possible, please try to park before you reach the intersection to save on congestion and choose a spot as far away as you feel comfortable walking from, leaving closer spots to those who can’t walk as far.
The rally will start on the SE corner, but as more folks arrive, we will disperse to the SW, NW, and NE corners, as well.   If you cross from one side to another, please pay particular attention to cars turning right as you cross! 
 Participants should bring their own signs (if they want to hold them).  Note that sticks supporting the signs can’t be pointed at either end.  Also, in designing content for the signs, please remember that children will be present.  
Please stand only along the sidewalks parallel to the street and not on the grass.  However, also be sure to allow pedestrian access to the sidewalk and businesses.   We are not expecting issues, but keep in mind that a core principle behind our events is a commitment to nonviolent action.  Remember to de-escalate any potential confrontation with someone,  who disagrees with you. And of course, follow directions from our excellent Lenexa police, if asked.
We will not have speakers. The plan will simply be to hold the signs we have made and wave, if that feels right.  We expect that a lot of passing cars will honk back in approval! 
Finally, please note that all our organizers will be wearing lanyards with badges reading  “Standing Rally Corner Captain or “Standing Rally Media/City Liaison”.  If you see other folks with “Press” marked on their clothing or who are giving direction to you, know that they are not part of Four Corners and are not endorsed or vetted by us.
See you soon.  Let’s show our neighbors “what Democracy Looks Like”!!
P.S.  If you want to post an inspiring (!) story about your experience, please add #FourCornersinLenexa to your post!

title: Hands Across Chicagoland
description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens as we form a human chain of conscience across Chicagoland in peaceful protest against Trump’s illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defend the Constitution. 

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street and California Ave to Douglass Park. This is a peaceful protest. We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Please go to www.handsacrosschi.com and enter your zip code to get an assigned location along the route. This is important so that we can spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people closer to where they live. ***Ignore the map below; that is not your assigned location***

President Trump has defied court orders and forcibly sent people to a torture dungeon in El Salvador without a hearing or due process. Now he claims he’s unable to bring them back. He's ignored court rulings and arrested judges. If he can do this to them, he can do it to anyone.

These are the actions of a dictator—not a democratically elected president. Silence is not an option. When leaders cross the line into authoritarianism, it’s up to us—the people—to push back. This protest is about more than politics. It's about defending basic human dignity, civil liberties, and the idea that no one is above the law.

Bring your family, friends, neighbors, coworkers—anyone who believes in freedom and democracy.

title: Weekly Peaceful Solidarity Rally
description: Join Lake Region Indivisible weekly on Wednesday mornings for a peaceful rally of solidarity in opposition to the Trump Regime

title: 5/7 Stop Elon Musk Rally!
description:
Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership! 

Unvetted DOGE operatives hired by Musk are accessing our data, impounding funds allocated by Congress, and crippling federal agencies. This empowers the surveillance state and paves the way for billionaire tax cuts, deregulation and more. 

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood - not in business parking lots. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change.Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will call law enforcement if needed to shut down such unauthorized activity.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.

accessibility_notes: Street side location.Possibly parking at the office building  but reserve those for our people with mobility restrictions if you can and park at the nearby mall.

title: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
description:
For May 11 protest:

Meet in the public lot behind the Flanders Professional Building. It’s in the middle of the block bordered by NW 22nd and 23rd, and NW Everett and Flanders.

Please back into a spot by 1:45 so you’re positioned to pull into the caravan when we leave at 2:00. 

The 5/11 route will have some slow stretches with quite quite a few pauses at lights and intersections. We use these pauses as part of the protest: shout, chant, show your signs, pass out pamphlets or buttons, etc. We do get split up, but we all get back together at the end of these stretches. We’ll talk about traffic and safety and a few tips to keep it all together at 1:45.
The 5/11 PDX Car Caravan Protest will end at the ICE building in S Portland. A Mother’s Day Vigil and Memorial will be held there at 4:00, which is close to our ETA. You are invited to join this additional protest put on by PDX Contra las Deportaciones to protest and remember the victims of the Trump administration’s cruel abductions and deportations.



This a local Indivisible event!

PDX Car Caravan Protest 1.0 was active weekly or more for over a year, 2020-21, and protested racial injustice and police brutality. We are back in version 2.0 as a raucous motorized protest for people who love justice and hate injustice of all varieties. If you are outraged and need to protest but for whatever reason don’t (always)do crowds, standing and marching, roll with us. Keep your foot on the gas. 

More details on bluesky and Facebook: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
accessibility_notes: You arrive and can remain in your own vehicle for the entire protest. We give a short traffic safety orientation and provide a written handout. If you need to remain in your vehicle during the orientation, just let us know so we can make sure you can access the information.

Going for another round folks. Same time, same great location.

title: NO KINGS! TAKE BACK THE FLAG!
description:
FLAG DAY 2025!
MAGA has tried to use our flag to spread hate and division.
But that's not our flag!
Our flag represents hope, freedom and the sacrifices of generations of Americans.
It's time to take back the flag!! FLAG DAY 2025!
In America, we don’t put up with would-be kings. NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption from Trump and his allies. We’ve watched as they’ve cracked down on free speech, detained people for their political views, threatened to deport American citizens, and defied the courts. They’ve done this all while continuing to serve and enrich their billionaire allies.

🚨On Saturday, June 14, we’re taking to the streets nationwide. We’re not gathering to feed his ego. We’re building a movement that leaves him behind.🚨

The flag doesn’t belong to Donald Trump. It belongs to us. We’re not watching history happen. We’re making it.

On June 14th, we’re showing up everywhere he isn’t—to say no thrones, no crowns, no kings.
accessibility_notes: There are elevators at all of the intersections.If you are not able or choose not to march, feel free to rally in front of NYNY.

The Department of Veterans' Affairs is planning to cut 83,000 jobs at the agency that provides healthcare for millions of veterans. 
Tell them "Hands Off Our Vets!"

title: Protest at John Cornyn’s Houston Office
description:
Join other Houstonians in protesting outside John Cornyn’s Houston office (on Memorial Drive) to raise awareness of your objection to recent government actions.

Signs available or make your own.

*Do not park in 5300 Memorial garage*

The Cornyn Houston Office Protest has been on Houston streets each Tuesday for over 8 years. Fully independent, the Cornyn Protest has been sustained by a dedicated core of Houstonians. The protest sets the example of people showing up for themselves no matter what.

title: SACRAMENTO FIGHT FOR SCHOOLS
description: Join Sacramento educators and allies to stand up for students and defend public education. We're gathering to fight back against attacks on our students, educators, and communities launched by the Trump/Musk administration. Sponsored by the CTA and supported by INDIVISIBLE Sacramento. Concurrent events in San Francisco, LA, and San Diego.

title: Large Message Board Display at 53rd Overcrossing
description:
This is a local Indivisible event in NE Portland on the 53rd Avenue freeway overcrossing next to Providence Hospital.

Come join in the fun - wave flags, carry you own signs, help put up large letterboards for rush-hour traffic visibility. Messages will change while staying relevant to the latest news of the current regime's ongoing violations of human rights and the US Constitution.  Signs you carry are best made two-sided and with letters as large as possible to be readable through the one-inch vertical bars. Meet and socialize afterward at the New Deal Cafe a half-mile north.
accessibility_notes: Outdoors - so dress for the weather.

title: Vigil for Black Lives - Dimond District
description: This a local Indivisible event! Neighbors for Racial Justice has held a weekly Vigil for Black Lives for the past decade at Fruitvale & MacArthur in Oakland. We’d love for you to join us! People have told us our weekly presence challenges gaslighting, shows solidarity with our Black neighbors, gives drivers an opportunity to honk their support (& since Jan 20, protest Trump) to the whole intersection. We've added a couple new signs with broader focus.

title: TRUST Act Now - InterFaith Day of Action
description:
Our many religious, spiritual, and ethical traditions teach us that we have a moral imperative to welcome the stranger, provide for those in need, and protect the vulnerable in our communities. 

That’s where we’re inviting faith leaders and all people of conscience to join us at the CT State Capitol, for a Faith Day of Action at the Capitol Building to talk with legislators about why they MUST protect our immigrant communities and pass a strengthened TRUST Act.

The TRUST Act (HB 7212) is a bill that would protect our CT immigrant community from ICE abductions and protect CT local resources from being used to further mass deportations.

The Trust Act will send a strong message that Connecticut protects the safety and humanity of all its residents, regardless of immigration status. 

**Schedule for the the day:**

- Press conference: 10:30am-11:15am

- Training: 11:30am-12pm

- Talking with legislators 12pm - 2pm

*Never been to the Capitol before or spoken with legislators?* No worries! We’ll provide you with all the materials you need and we’ll have TRUST Act Now! Coalition leaders present to guide all attendees!

title: Protest Avelo Airlines’ Plan to Carry Out Deportation Flights - ONGOING
description:
Avelo Airlines has accepted a $150 million contract to operate deportation flights, aiding in the illegal removal of individuals without their right to a fair hearing or due process. This is not only inhumane but a direct violation of our Constitution. 

We’re calling for a full boycott of Avelo Airlines and organizing protests a weekly protest at our local airport. 

We will be on the sidewalk leading to the Charles M. Schulz Sonoma County Airport, which is for now a hub for Avelo's flights at a time when a maximum number of travelers will see our protest. It is also a good opportunity to protest federal layoffs with the FAA.

You can park nearby or take SMART to get there.

title: Friday Rally to Protect  Democracy in Mentor OH
description:
Join us for a weekly rally to protect democracy. 

We will stand along Mentor Avenue with signs and flags.   We will peacefully show that we object to the insidious cuts to vital federal programs and employees, the abduction of immigrants, and the racist policies conducted by the Trump administration.  

District 14 members will have the opportunity to fill out comment sheets for Congressman Dave Joyce.  

Bring signs, friends, and family.  

Each week we will donate food to a local food bank.     Please bring canned protein, whole grains, pasta, cereal, peanut butter and jam, and toilet paper, paper towels, and tissues   

Donating is optional.  

This event is sponsored by Indivisible, 50501, Progress NEO, District 14 Voice, Like Minded in Lake County, and the District 14 Democrats—Ashtabula, Geauga, Lake, Portage, and Trumbull counties.  

Note—this event was formerly titled ‘Where’s Congressman Joyce.”   Though the title had changed, we still wonder where he is.

title: Step Up CD-8: Peoria Protest (Lake Pleasant Pkwy & Happy Valley Rd)
description:
📍 **Location:** Lake Pleasant Pkwy & Happy Valley Rd.  
🗓 **Date:** Saturday, May 10, 2025  
⏰ **Time:** 8:00 AM – 9:30 AM  


(Looking for a different Step Up location? Go to [linktr.ee/stepupcd8](https://linktr.ee/stepupcd8).)  


We’re standing up to **Donald Trump** because **Rep. Abe Hamadeh won’t**!  


Join your neighbors for a peaceful, high-visibility protest as part of the **Step Up CD-8 multi-site protest**.  


While Trump and his billionaire friends dismantle our government for their own personal gain, CD-8 Congressman **Abe Hamadeh has been hiding from constituents** behind closed-door events with donors and MAGA voters.  


For months, concerned constituents across CD-8 have asked Rep. Abe Hamadeh to hold a public town hall and listen to the concerns of the people he was elected to represent. Instead, we’ve been met with silence — and even **threats of arrest**.  


When we demonstrated peacefully outside his office, his staff **had a senior adult woman’s car towed**. When our numbers grew, Hamadeh coordinated with GOP counter-protestors to **obstruct our access to a public sidewalk**.  


**It’s clear: Hamadeh answers to Trump, not to us.**  


So on **May 10**, we’re taking the message to five cities across CD-8:  
**Enough.**  

---

### We'll be at the following locations:

- Lake Pleasant Pkwy & Happy Valley Rd in **Peoria**
- Anthem Way & Gavilan Peak Pkwy in **Anthem**
- Civic Center Dr. & Bell Rd in **Surprise**
- 99th Ave & Bell Rd in **Sun City**
- 35th Ave & Peoria in **Phoenix**

---

### Here’s what we need you to do:

- Bring signs (see sign ideas below)  

- Wear sun protection  

- Stay hydrated  

- Be respectful and nonviolent  


---

This coordinated effort is powered by a coalition of grassroots groups:  
**Northwest Valley Indivisible, Anthem Indivisible, Desert Progressives, The Pushback Club,** and **The Big Blue Bubble.**  


Together, we’re standing up for democracy and demanding real accountability in Arizona’s 8th Congressional District.  


---

### Sign Ideas:

- Stop the Billionaire Give-Away  

- Hands Off Social Security *(or ...Vaccines, ...Medicare, …Medicaid, …Education, ...the VA, …AHCCCS, etc.)*

title: Accountability Tuesdays - Jeff Van Drew has got to go!
description:
**Accountability Tuesdays: Van Drew, Meet with Us**

WE ARE DEMANDING A TOWN HALL - The excuse is that his district is too big and so all we get is tele town halls - 

**Host:**  
Atlantic County Indivisible

**When:**  
**Tuesday, April 29 2025 — 4:30 PM**  
(Repeats every other Tuesday)

**Where:**  
**Jeff Van Drew’s District Office** 

Northfield Office

1001 Tilton Road
Suite 101
Northfield, NJ 08225
Phone: (609) 625-5008

**Event Description:**  
Congressman Jeff Van Drew is supposed to represent **us**—but he only meets with **donors**, **special interests**, and **MAGA extremists**.

He hasn’t held a public town hall in years, and his voting record speaks for itself:
- **Voted against certifying the 2020 election results**
- Opposed **abortion rights**, **student loan forgiveness**, and **LGBTQ+ protections**
- Supports efforts to **defund public education** and deny the climate crisis
- Turns his back on working people and silences dissent in our district

So we show up. Peacefully. Persistently. Every other Tuesday.

> **Donors get the meetings. Constituents get ignored.**

We’re rallying outside his **Northfield District Office** to demand visibility, accountability, and representation. This is a **peaceful protest** to let our neighbors—and our congressman—know we are watching.

**What to Bring:**
- Signs (or use ours!)  
- Friends, neighbors, coworkers  
- Water, weather-appropriate clothing  
- Your voice and your presence  

**Accessibility:**  
- Public sidewalk with parking nearby  
- No marching—stand or sit as long as you’d like  
- Family-friendly and open to all

We’ve coordinated with local police to ensure a safe, orderly, nonviolent demonstration. Everyone who believes in democracy is welcome.

title: MAY DAY: WOODSTOCK WORKERS RISING
description:
📣 EVENT UPDATE – PLEASE READ

Due to the forecast of severe thunderstorms on Saturday, we are rescheduling the “May Day: Woodstock Workers Rising” protest to Saturday, May 10.
🕓 Same time
📍 Same location
🛟 Same safety protocols and logistics—unless otherwise noted
☀️ The weather for May 10 is expected to be clear and rain-free.

BUT—we’re still gathering this weekend.

Instead of protesting in the storm, we’re inviting everyone to join us indoors at the Artists’ Spring Art Showcase at the Artisan Resource Center in Marietta. It’s a huge, open, community-driven space filled with local art, open studios, and a handmade artisan market—just in time for Mother’s Day.

🎨 Saturday, May 3 — 10am to 6pm
📍 585 Cobb Pkwy SE, Marietta, GA 30060
🎟️ Free & open to the public
🔗 http://www.artisanresourcecenter.net/events.html

Why this matters:
Fascism always targets art. Creators challenge power, build culture, and make resistance visible. Showing up for artists is showing up for freedom. In an era of censorship, tariffs, and corporate monopolies, our local artists need solidarity—and you just might find better deals than at a big box store.

Thanks for staying grounded, flexible, and focused on what we’re building together.
See you this weekend—and next.

—Indivisible Woodstock CAN

🛠 DRESS THE PART. BRING A SIGN. STAND WITH WORKERS.

This May Day, we stand together as the people who keep this town running—workers who teach our kids, care for the sick, grow our food, build our homes, and serve our neighbors.

No matter your job or background, we all deserve a fair shot: fair pay, personal freedom, safe communities, and leaders who work for us, not just for billionaires and backroom lobbyists.

Too many of those freedoms are being chipped away—by people in power who treat workers like a cost to cut, not a voice to listen to.

We say no more.

👕 Dress up as a worker—your job, or one you admire.
🪧 Make a sign that shows what that worker deserves—and what’s at risk.

👨‍👩‍👧 This is a peaceful, family-friendly protest.
✊Wear red, white, and blue to show we are the real patriots.
🚫 No profanity on signs—our message is strong without it.

--------------

🛠 WHAT IS MAY DAY?

May Day—International Workers’ Day—honors the people who built this country.

It began with American workers striking in 1886 for the eight-hour workday. When police opened fire on protesters at Chicago’s Haymarket Square, it became a global symbol of the fight for dignity on the job.

Governments around the world now recognize May 1st as a day to stand with labor. But in the U.S., we’ve been told to forget.

We remember. May Day belongs to us. And we’re reclaiming it.

--------------

🧍🏽‍♀️ EXAMPLES: LOCAL WORKERS, LOCAL POWER

🛒 Retail Worker (Publix, Target, Home Depot) with a sign that says, “We stock your shelves. Don’t empty our paychecks.”

👩🏽‍⚕️ Healthcare Worker (Nurse, Tech, Aide) with a sign that says, “We care for your family. Let us care for ours.”

📚 Teacher or School Staff with a sign that says, “Let us teach. Keep politics out of the classroom.”

🍽 Restaurant or Food Service Worker with a sign that says, “We served through the storm. We deserve better.”

💼 Office Worker / Business Services with a sign that says, “We’re not overhead. We’re the engine.”

👷 Construction Worker with a sign that says, “We build Woodstock. Give us a future here.”

⚙️ Manufacturing or Warehouse Worker with a sign that says, “We move the goods. Respect the hands behind the supply chain.”

--------------

✊ WHAT TO EXPECT:

We’ll line up peacefully along the sidewalk in downtown Woodstock with signs and costumes

This is a legal, unpermitted protest: we will obey all laws and exercise our First Amendment rights without blocking traffic or pedestrians

--------------

🔧 HOW TO JOIN:

- Pick your worker costume
- Make your sign (no profanity)
- Wear red, white, and blue

📍 Meeting location will be announced soon.

RSVP & follow for updates:

Instagram: @indivisiblewoodstockcan

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61573799888446

Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/woodstockcan.bsky.social

May Day isn’t a memory. It’s a movement.
This is our moment to show who really makes this town strong. Not Wall Street. Not the lobbyists. The workers. The people. Us.

Want to get ready before the protest? Join us for the MAY DAY Prep Party on Friday, May 2nd! We’ll make signs, prep banners, go over our plan, and connect with others who are ready to rise. Snacks, music, and solidarity. RSVP here: https://www.mobilize.us/indivisible/event/782309/

title: Tesla Takedown Protest in Seaside, Ca
description:
Join us EVERY Saturday at 12pm to protest Elon Musk and his unconstitutional dismantling of the federal government. Bring a sign, your friends, musical instruments, whatever makes you happy.

*** Please be aware that we'e seen some counter protestors at these events. They're mostly loud and obnoxious, trying to provoke a response. The best thing to do is ignore them entirely and not give them the attention they crave. ***

We have more people every week! It's a good time and we get a lot of positive feedback from passing cars. It might seem like a small thing but every little bit helps. And it feels good to DO SOMETHING so come on down!

Elon Musk and DOGE are engaged in an administrative coup of the federal government. They have taken control of the federal payment system and are unilaterally suspending funds appropriated by congress, in clear violation of the Constitution.

They have already caused immense harm by dismantling USAID and have set their sights on everything from the Social Security to the NIH and the FAA next. Make no mistake, their end goal is the destruction of the US Federal Government and its ability to check corporate power and provide basic services.

How this develops in Washington remains to be seen, but as US citizens we can exercise our 1st Amendment right to peacefully protest. Elon Musk's liquid net worth is largely based on Tesla stock, which is currently valued at 10-15 times that of other car companies. Driving down the share price is a direct attack on Elon's power.

The stakes couldn’t be higher. No one is coming to save us—not politicians, not the media. It's up to the people to stand up and fight for democracy and against fascism.

title: MAY DAY: WOODSTOCK WORKERS RISING
description:
📣 EVENT UPDATE – PLEASE READ

Due to the forecast of severe thunderstorms on Saturday, we are rescheduling the “May Day: Woodstock Workers Rising” protest to **Saturday, May 10**.

🕓 Same time
📍 Same location
🛟 Same safety protocols and logistics—unless otherwise noted
☀️ The weather for May 10 is expected to be clear and rain-free.

***BUT—we’re still gathering this weekend.***

Instead of protesting in the storm, we’re inviting everyone to join us indoors at the ***Artists’ Spring Art Showcase at the Artisan Resource Center in Marietta***. It’s a huge, open, community-driven space filled with local art, open studios, and a handmade artisan market—just in time for Mother’s Day.

🎨 Saturday, May 3 — ***10am to 6pm***
📍 585  Cobb  Parkway  South, Marietta, GA 30060
🎟️ Free & open to the public
🔗 http://www.artisanresourcecenter.net/events.html

Why this matters:
Fascism always targets art. Creators challenge power, build culture, and make resistance visible. Showing up for artists is showing up for freedom. In an era of censorship, tariffs, and corporate monopolies, our local artists need solidarity—and you just might find better deals than at a big box store.

Thanks for staying grounded, flexible, and focused on what we’re building together.

***See you this weekend—and next.***
—Indivisible Woodstock CAN


🛠 DRESS THE PART. BRING A SIGN. STAND WITH WORKERS.

This May Day, we stand together as the people who keep this town running—workers who teach our kids, care for the sick, grow our food, build our homes, and serve our neighbors.

No matter your job or background, we all deserve a fair shot: fair pay, personal freedom, safe communities, and leaders who work for us, not just for billionaires and backroom lobbyists.

Too many of those freedoms are being chipped away—by people in power who treat workers like a cost to cut, not a voice to listen to.

We say no more.

👕 Dress up as a worker—your job, or one you admire. 🪧 Make a sign that shows what that worker deserves—and what’s at risk.

👨‍👩‍👧 This is a peaceful, family-friendly protest. ✊Wear red, white, and blue to show we are the real patriots. 🚫 No profanity on signs—our message is strong without it.

🛠 WHAT IS MAY DAY?

May Day—International Workers’ Day—honors the people who built this country.

It began with American workers striking in 1886 for the eight-hour workday. When police opened fire on protesters at Chicago’s Haymarket Square, it became a global symbol of the fight for dignity on the job.

Governments around the world now recognize May 1st as a day to stand with labor. But in the U.S., we’ve been told to forget.

We remember. May Day belongs to us. And we’re reclaiming it.

🧍🏽‍♀️ EXAMPLES: LOCAL WORKERS, LOCAL POWER

🛒 Retail Worker (Publix, Target, Home Depot) with a sign that says, “We stock your shelves. Don’t empty our paychecks.”

👩🏽‍⚕️ Healthcare Worker (Nurse, Tech, Aide) with a sign that says, “We care for your family. Let us care for ours.”

📚 Teacher or School Staff with a sign that says, “Let us teach. Keep politics out of the classroom.”

🍽 Restaurant or Food Service Worker with a sign that says, “We served through the storm. We deserve better.”

💼 Office Worker / Business Services with a sign that says, “We’re not overhead. We’re the engine.”

👷 Construction Worker with a sign that says, “We build Woodstock. Give us a future here.”

⚙️ Manufacturing or Warehouse Worker with a sign that says, “We move the goods. Respect the hands behind the supply chain.”

✊ WHAT TO EXPECT:

We’ll line up peacefully along the sidewalk in downtown Woodstock with signs and costumes

This is a legal, unpermitted protest: we will obey all laws and exercise our First Amendment rights without blocking traffic or pedestrians

🔧 HOW TO JOIN:

Pick your worker costume
Make your sign (no profanity)
Wear red, white, and blue
📍 Meeting location will be announced soon.

RSVP & follow for updates:

Instagram: @indivisiblewoodstockcan

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61573799888446

Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/woodstockcan.bsky.social

May Day isn’t a memory. It’s a movement. This is our moment to show who really makes this town strong. Not Wall Street. Not the lobbyists. The workers. The people. Us.

title: No Veteran Left Behind | A Memorial Day Silent Protest
description:
This is a SILENT protest to bring visibility to and honor our Veterans hosted by Indivisible Acworth. We invite our community to stand in solidarity with our veterans.

We are hosting a silent protest on Sunday, May 25th at the Cobb VA North Clinic in Marietta to raise awareness regarding the assault to veterans' benefits, entitlements, and access to care. 

On Thursday, the US Department of Veterans Affairs ended a mortgage rescue program that has helped almost 20,000 veterans avoid foreclosure and keep their homes. Approximately 90,000 VA loans are at risk of foreclosure and this number continues to increase as more and more veterans are illegally terminated from their Federal jobs by DOGE. 

If the administration can cut this program, reduce vital staff, and create restrictions to the Suicide Hotline, what else do they plan to cut? 

We must gather in solidarity behind the veteran community and we must stand up and fight in memory of the veterans who stood up to, and lost their lives in their combat against fascism and human rights violations.

Because Memorial Day is a solemn day of remembrance, we ask that protestors do not scream and that signage remains RESPECTFUL and relates ONLY to cuts to veterans programs, supporting our veterans, supporting VA staff, and signs that honor the fallen and defend the living.

Sign ideas include, but are not limited to: ﻿﻿﻿﻿

﻿"Honor the Fallen. Care for the Living."﻿﻿
"They Fought for Us — Now We Fight for Them."
"Cuts to VA = Dishonor to Their Sacrifice."
"Memorial Day Is More Than Words — Fund the VA!"
﻿"Project 2025: Betraying the Oath to Those Who Took One."
"Protect the VA, Protect the Promise."
"Fully Staff the VA — Lives Depend on It."
"No More Delays. No More Cuts. No More Excuses."
"Veterans Before Politics."
"We Lost Brothers/Sisters in War — Don’t Lose Them to Policy."
"No Vet Should Fight for Benefits They Earned in Combat."﻿﻿
"From Battlefield to Bureaucracy — Stop the War on Veterans."
"Veterans Deserve Dignity, Not Budget Cuts."

Again, please keep signs respectful. There is a time and place for more humorous or abrasive messaging, but we are showing solidarity with our vets.

title: CD 22- VALADAO - Save Kern Medical Hospital from Medicaid Cuts!
description:
The Republican led Congress is proposing to make devastating cuts to healthcare programs which could impact 15 million Californians, including children and people with disabilities!  And they're making the cuts to give huge tax breaks to millionaires and billionaires.

Many hospitals around the state could lose major funding. Kern Medical Hospital receives 72% of it's funding through Medicaid.  The proposed cuts would mean devastating cutbacks in services and longer wait times - even for people who have private insurance.  

To stop the cuts and save lives we need to get a handful of Republican Congressmembers to vote NO on the proposed healthcare cuts.  We'll be rallying to save Kern Medical Hospital on Tuesday, May 13th at 11:30 am with doctors, nurses, other healthcare providers and community supporters to call on Congressman David Valadao to vote NO on any cuts to Medicaid!

After you sign up, you will get a confirmation email. It will include an option to "Contact the organizer." title: Stop the Billionaires
description:
Why is Mike Lawler not standing up to Elon Musk? Why isn't Lawler stopping Musk from cutting Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid? Why is Lawler choosing "DOGE" over our country? Maybe its the $1.7 million (million!) dollars Elon Musk paid Lawler for this past campaign alone. Join us Saturday for an extra special Lawler - Musk Takedown!"

We are taking action at this Tesla-owned dealership. We are asking people to line the sidewalks in front of the dealership in a peaceful protest. This dealership is a few blocks from the MetroNorth station in Mt Kisco. We will be there from 1 to 3 p.m. on Saturdays. Bring a sign (a folding chair if you want). Bring the kids.

Our nation is under attack from within. The time to yell at the news or tune out the world is over. We need to stand up now, or soon, we won’t be able to. I cannot tell you what to do, but I have spent my Saturdays in front of the Tesla-owned dealership in Northern Westchester, protesting the destruction of our democracy.

Please join us on Saturdays from 1 to 3. Bring your best signs and bring friends. It is letting the public know our opposition to this theft of our democracy and the rampant corruption that entails. We can also show our strong opposition to abandoning global friends and surrendering to our enemies.

title: Sat, 5/17 > Elon Takedown Western MA - Sidewalk Protest at Tesla Supercharger Location

location.venue: Public Sidewalks adjacent to Pride property

description:
### Event is 1pm - 3pm.

### Event is on, rain or shine

There's no such thing as "bad" weather....just poor clothing choices!

### Why are we doing this?

Elon's busy wreaking havoc, and we're busy letting our fellow citizens and elected officials know how we feel about it.

What's the message?
Elon Musk is an unelected political actor. He's causing tremendous damage to our government, and is hurting people who work(ed) for governmental agencies, and people who are served by governmental agencies. Elon Musk is hurting our country and its people.

We are here to draw attention to Musk's role as a political figure, and to highlight that his (and others') actions are illegal, hurtful and morally wrong. 

From Tesla Takedown:
"Tesla Takedown is a peaceful protest movement. We oppose interference with others' rights to go about their business, violence, vandalism, and destruction of property. 

This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly."

### On blocking the Tesla chargers...DON'T DO IT.

Please do not block the Tesla chargers with your vehicles. It's not OK. We don't want to inconvenience Tesla owners, most of whom bought their Teslas to protect the planet. In exercising our rights, we will not impinge on the rights of others.

### Parking

Please don't park on the Pride property. Parking is available:

- at Hadley Crossing, just east of the Bay Rd. intersection

- along the side of Bay Rd.

- at the vacant gas station just west of Pride

- at Hampton Inn Village Shops, 41-49 Russell Street

### Remember our goals!

- to be in community with other pro-democracy folks!

- to grow in numbers and courage and resilience

- to attract others to join us 

- to ready ourselves for the coming General Strikes

- to be kind, and have fun!

title: We the People on Peoples Street

This is a peaceful protest, so let’s keep it calm and respectful. 🌿 Here’s how you can help:

✅ Stay peaceful—don’t engage with hecklers or counter-protesters.  
✅ Don’t block entrances, exits, bus stops, or sidewalks.  
✅ If you bring chairs, keep them on the grass.  
✅ For your safety, please stay off the road.

**There's a Core Group that is always present —unless it’s raining!** ☔  
Whether you’re a regular or a first-timer, we’ll stand together and make our voices heard! We'll make you feel welcome.

Come be part of the movement! 🌟 #WeThePeopleOnPeoplesStreet #Indivisible #PeacefulProtest #StandTogether

Consistent visibility is how we grow resistance and how we win.

Together we can do this.

Indivisible 515 Team

title: Tues. 5/13 > I-91 Overpass Standout - 9 Mtn Park Rd, Holyoke, MA
description:
Come out to show that ordinary people can raise their voices against the chaos and destruction of this Administration. Help remind folks that they, too, can stand up for their beliefs - and that there's lots and lots of people who aren't on board with the "cruelty as entertainment" behavior of Trump and Musk and the GOP.

Family-friendly!

### How to Get There

The address "9 Mountain Park Rd, Holyoke" will get you there if you're using Waze. (Mountain Park Road runs off Route 5, and is not accessible from I-91.) People have reported that some GPS systems bring you right under the bridge, but on I-91. That’s annoying!

Please park on the side of the road before the bridge. We can't park on the bridge.

### Other Stuff

Please take everything you brought away with you, and leave the site totally clean.

If rain is predicted, we'll cancel. If we cancel, you'll receive an email notification.

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational in words and body language.

### A Few Requests

We've found that roof rake sections make wonderful flagpoles and banner poles. If you have a roof rake (or 10’-15’ light metal poles or conduit) to contribute, we'll be happy to take it off your hands!

Donations...we've purchased banners and grommets and flags and zip ties and bungee cords, and we'll be getting more. We’ve purchased 20” x 30” letter boards for messaging we can change. All this costs $$$. We'll have a bucket for donations, and if you could throw something in, that'd be great. And if not, that's perfectly OK, too - your presence is what's really important. See where the money's going! https://tinyurl.com/IN-SLWMProtestTeamFinancials

title: Columbus Mothers and Others Standing Against Fascism
description:
On Saturday, May 10, join us in Columbus to say no to the bullies and billionaires who are threatening our freedoms and disappearing residents from our streets. 

In honor of Mother's Day weekend, and as part of actions happening throughout the state, we invite mothers and others to join us in standing up and speaking out against fascism.

We will have speakers, music, sign language interpretation, a great sound system, and an opportunity to march. Please join us at Bicentennial Park as we build momentum against Trump, Musk, and the hostile takeover of our government.

title: Stand Up for Democracy March and Rally
description:
Join Democracy Action Network (DAN) for a powerful day of democratic engagement, community solidarity, and peaceful action. 

On Flag Day 2025, we stand together to reaffirm our commitment to democratic principles, constitutional governance, and human rights for all.

In a time when democratic institutions face unprecedented challenges, we invite concerned citizens of all backgrounds, beliefs, and political affiliations to unite in defense of our shared democratic values. This nonpartisan rally brings together speakers, community leaders, and grassroots activists to inspire action and build momentum for democratic renewal.

The Stand Up for Democracy Rally and March will feature:

- Keynote addresses from prominent civil rights advocates and democracy experts
- Community-led workshops on civic engagement and grassroots organizing
- Interactive educational displays about democratic principles and voting rights
- Family-friendly activities and entertainment
- A peaceful march from Palisades Park to Santa Monica City Hall

Democracy isn't just something we have—it's something we do. Join us as we stand up for the democratic principles that unite us as Americans: equality under the law, freedom of expression, fair elections, and government that answers to its people.

Transportation: The Downtown Santa Monica Metro E Line station provides direct rail access from Downtown LA and is a short walk from the rally site. Additional bus service and bike parking will be available.

Accessibility: The event is fully accessible, with accommodations for all participants.

For more information: Visit democracyactionnetwork.org/standup2025 or email info@democracyactionnetwork.org

The Democracy Action Network (DAN) is a nonpartisan grassroots organization founded in 2024 dedicated to defending democratic institutions, promoting civic engagement, and fostering inclusive democracy through nonviolent action and community empowerment.
#StandUpForDemocracy #DemocracyMatters #PeacefulAction

title: White Rose Rally!
description:
May 9th commemorates the  White Rose Movement,  a student led non-violent resistance group that urged the German people to oppose Hitler and his fascist regime.

“We will not be silent,” was the powerful  statement used by the White Rose in Nazi Germany. And we cannot be silent today.

After listening to speakers in front of City Hall, participants will spread out along the sidewalks of Main Street downtown to proclaim our message of resistance.

For more information:
Read John Paradis’ column about the White Rose in the Daily Hampshire Gazette,  https://www.gazettenet.com/Guest-columnist-Paradis-60543852;

Visit the National World War II Museum webpage on Sophie Scholl and the White Rose, https://www.nationalww2museum.org/war/articles/sophie-scholl-and-white-rose;

For information about Indivisible Northampton/Swing Left Western Mass visit the website https://in-slwm.org

title: NO KINGS - Boston Pride
description:
June 14th has been called as the next 50501 and Indivisible National Day of Action. This is Trump’s birthday and it is also the date of Boston Pride. 

[Mass 50501](http://mass50501.com) invites other aligned orgs to help amplify Pride by encouraging all chapters to sign up to march and individuals to attend. We will not stand idly by while our queer and transgender brothers, sisters and nonbinary siblings are erased by this administration.

🚨 We’re fighting for democracy. Let’s make them listen.

title: Stop the Cuts-Middletown Rally at Congressman Chris Smith's Office of Event
description:
This a local Indivisible event!

Republicans including Chris Smith are selling us out to help billionaires like Elon Musk get even richer. They’re planning to slash funding to Medicaid, SNAP, and other vital programs to give massive tax cuts to these billionaires. So we're using our voices and heading to Chris Smith's office to tell him "No Cuts".

We'll be rallying on the grassy area in front of Chris Smith's office on Route 35 so we can be seen by passing motorists.

This is intended to be a friendly and peaceful rally. First time activists are especially welcome.

Bring your signs, American flags, noisemakers, musical instruments and protest music.

If you would like to stop into Mr. Smith’s Middletown office to leave a message or tell your story, you’ll need to call ahead to schedule an appointment: (732)780-3035.

title: Victory Red Day
description:
A campaign for a Day of Female Solidarity and Empowerment on June 24, 2025—the anniversary of Roe v. Wade’s repeal. The idea is simple yet powerful: women and supporters of women everywhere wear red lipstick as a symbol of strength, resilience, and the ongoing fight for gender equality.

Victory Red lipstick has long been a symbol of women’s power, particularly during World War II, when it was worn by women on the home front to represent strength, defiance, and patriotism. During this time, women stepped into roles previously held by men, contributing to the war effort while asserting their independence and resilience. They stood against facism, all while maintaining households and duties outside of their normal realm.

title: Wednesday Movement Sign Wave in Lauraville (Rain or Shine)
description:
The Wednesday Movement launched on March 12, 2025 when disgruntled seniors took to the streets in Baltimore to make their feelings known. The Movement, a weekly Pro-Democracy, Anti-Trump, Anti-Putin vigil, gathers on a heavily trafficked Baltimore street corner on Wednesday evenings.

We invite others who feel the same way to join the Movement. You do not need to be old, you do not need to be in Baltimore, and you do not need to stand on Wednesdays, but we ask that you use the Wednesday Movement banner.

It’s easy:​ Reach out to friends and neighbors​. Make some signs (one should say “We Are The Wednesday Movement)​. Pick a day, time, and location that works for your group. And spread the word!  This is a grassroots initiative. It has the potential to change the world. Join with us and help make it happen!

The Lauraville Sign Wave will be held Rain or Shine but not if thunder/lightning are in the forecast.

Contact Anne George, 443-831-7528 for more information on initiating a sign wave in your area.

title: IndivisibleDALLAS: NO KINGS
description:
# NO KINGS is a national day of action and mass mobilization in response to the increasing authoritarian excesses and corruption of the Trump administration. 

Donald Trump thinks his rule is absolute, but in America, we don’t do “kings.” Since the inauguration, the Trump administration and its enablers have operated as though they have a mandate—but they don’t, and never did. They are going to extremes to empower Trump and enrich themselves, while cutting jobs and services for the rest of us. Now, they’re turning Flag Day into a celebration of Trump. 

We’re standing together against the abuses of power, cruelty, and corruption. 

On June 14, we gather to remind Trump and his enablers: America has NO KING!

Whether you're outraged by attacks on civil rights, skyrocketing costs, abductions and disappearances, the gutting of essential services, or the assault on free speech—this moment is for you. Whether you've been in the fight for years or you're just fed up and ready to take action—this moment is for you.

title: OPEN DOORS, OPEN MINDS: Support Our Libraries and Museums!

location.venue: Sidewalk in front of Shelburne town office building

description:
Join Champlain Valley Indivisible for a family-friendly rally in support of our libraries and museums on Friday, May 9 in Shelburne. 3:00pm - 5:30pm. Meet in front of the Shelburne town office building and we’ll spread out from there along Shelburne Road. Stop by for a few minutes or join us for a few hours!

In March, President Trump issued an Executive order directing the dismantling of the the Institute of Museum and Library Services (IMLS), as well as six other agencies. The announcement also orders the Office of Management and Budget to reject any budget requests from IMLS (and the other six named agencies) other than funds needed to shut down the agency. This week, Trump released his 2026 budget proposal, which calls for the wholesale elimination of the National Endowment for the Arts, the National Endowment for the Humanities, and the Corporation for Public Broadcasting, as well as several other federal and regional cultural agencies.

We believe Culture Counts, that it's important to preserve art and history and literature, among other things, and we want to support our local libraries and museums as much as possible. Saturday, May 10 is opening day for Shelburne Museum, so we are gathering in support of the museum and library on Friday, May 9. Please join your friends and neighbors for this peaceful rally - let’s show our library and museum how essential they are to our community! 

***Please do not park at the Pierson Library. Look for other parking in town.

Let’s do this!

Please DO NOT park in the Rite Aid Lot. There is parking at the Oakhurst Library. We will set up transportation to the Rite aid corner for those with mobility issues.

We are not an organization. If you choose to join us at any event that we announce, it is as an individual citizen, not as a member of any group.

title: Stand Up for Democracy on Shelburne Rd, South Burlington
description:
Join friends and neighbors during rush hour, to show our fellow citizens that we're standing up for democracy, standing up for the Constitution, and standing against the Trump Administration's chaos and lawlessness. 

Bring a sign or a flag, bring a cowbell or whistle, and bring a friend. This is a highly visible spot, with thousands of cars per hour. Our weekly presence gives hope and inspiration to passers by who have not yet resolved to take action. And everyone who attends draws fresh energy from one another and from the community response. 

All participants share the responsibility to keep this gathering safe and peaceful. Use the lights to cross Shelburne Rd; don't engage in negative exchanges with passing drivers, and stay on public property. This is a peaceful demonstration that falls under our First Amendment rights to public assembly and freedom of speech.

title: Hillsboro, Ohio- Mother’s Against Fascism
description:
We are postponed from May Day to May 10th: 
Together, we stand united for our human rights and all of our communities in front of the Common Pleas Court in Hillsboro, Ohio.

Uphold the Constitution.
End Executive overreach.
Liberty and Justice for all.

We are gathering from 12-3pm out front of the Common Pleas Court to be seen and have our voices heard. Restore our programs and do what is best for we, the people. Not Trump, not his billionaires and not our representatives. The more of us the louder we are. There will be speakers, sign holding and a march towards the end of the protest. Stop at our table to sign in and check out our resources we have put together for everyone. Snacks and waters are provided there too as well as informational sheet about our fundraising efforts.

Carpooling options will be available! We want you to be able to get there.

We are still looking for volunteers to join our security crew, if this is something you think you would be interested in please reach out. We are also coming up with a donation drive to help support our communities.

***More details on the agenda for the day coming soon.

Remember what we are focused on. Do not let agitators or aggressors get a negative rise out of us, they are only distracting us from our goal, our movement. If we are approached by such folks we will step back and chant protect the constitution and this is what community looks like.

There are 2 free public parking lots near the meeting location, 3 and 5 minute walks as well as 2 hour parking directly in front of where we will be. Please stay as long as you possibly can if not the whole protest time. We need as many there as we can for the entire time. Local media also likes to pop in and out and we want to make sure they see us in our entirety!

At our first rally we had 7 folks, our 2nd 30 folks and our third 150 folks! Let’s see how many of us we can get out there on May 1st. SAVE THE DATE and make sure to spread the word! Hope to see you there.👏🏼

title: "Moral Monday" Street Rally

address_lines: N. Main St. and W. Division St.

description:
Please join us in opposing cuts to essential safety net programs!

Please join us at weekly recurring  "Moral Monday" street rallies, alternating between Hudson WI and River Falls WI.

Our first “Moral Monday” street rally will be in Downtown Hudson on Monday May 5, from 4PM to 6PM, at the intersection of Second and Vine Streets, where we will hold signs and stand along the public sidewalks.

Our second “Moral Monday” street rally will be in River Falls on Monday May 12, from 4PM to 6PM, at the intersection of Main and Division Streets, where we will hold signs and stand along the public sidewalks.

Folks may join for part or all the two hours, and may bring their own signs or use signs we’ll have to share.

If the weather is bad—hard rain, high wind, and/or lightening—we’ll cancel that week’s rally.

Our "Moral Monday" street rallies are inspired and informed by work of the prominent North Carolina pastor and anti-poverty activist the Rev. William Barber, who founded the Center for Public Theology and Public Policy at Yale and now teaches there.

On the twelfth anniversary of his first "Moral Monday" demonstration, Monday April 28, 2025, Rev. Barber was arrested for praying against the Republican-led budget while in the Rotunda of our US Capitol. At a rally held before he entered the Rotunda to pray, Rev. Barber said: “Forty-three percent of women and almost half of all children are poor and low income. Somebody ought to say something … Somebody gotta challenge this budget.”

We are holding "Moral Monday" street rallies to voice our challenges.

We oppose Republican-approved Congressional budget resolutions that harm the poorest and most vulnerable of Americans in order to give more than $5-trillion in tax breaks to the richest and most privileged of Americans.

We oppose Trump/Musk budget proposals that eliminate or make draconian cuts to federal programs for child care, health research, education, housing assistance, community development, and the elderly.

These funding cuts and proposed budgets are not just public policy choices, they are moral choices. 

These funding cuts and proposed budgets are morally wrong, not just bad public policy choices. 

Please join with us to "say something" and "challenge this budget".

title: Fri. 5/16 > Mass Pike Overpass Standout - Southampton Rd (Routes 10/202), Westfield
description:
Wow! What a great location for a standout! A few of us tried it out on Friday, May 2. There's a full-size sidewalk on the west side, and a narrow sidewalk (kind of like the narrow sidewalk at Mountain Park Rd.) on the east side. The west side will accommodate more people than the east side.

There's lots and lots of traffic passing by. Southampton Road (Routes 10/202) is heavily traveled northbound and southbound, and the Mass Pike eastbound and westbound is below. Lots of honks and thumbs up and waves...and a few folks flying middle fingers. We smile and wave at them all! 

We'll have letterboards prepared for the lower part of the overpass fencing - the photo shows how that will look to folks passing on the Mass Pike. We're interacting with motorists on the Mass Pike, and on Southampton Road. We've discovered that the magic happens when we smile and wave to people!

Come when you can, and leave when you must. You needn't be present for the entire 2-hour standout.

### How to Get There

The address "130 Southampton Road, Westfield" will get you just north of the overpass. 

### Parking

We can't park in the Southampton Rd breakdown lane. There's a vacant business property three or four properties north of the bridge, and it seems that parking would be OK there.

It looks like The Wealth Technology Group has vacated their office at 130 Southampton Rd, but the internet says that other businesses are located there, so please be mindful if you decide to park there.

### Etiquette!

We don't give the finger to people who give the finger to us, or who say unpleasant things. We smile and wave to them, too. 

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational in words and body language.

### Other Stuff

Please take everything you brought away with you, and leave the site totally clean.

If rain is predicted, we'll cancel. If we cancel, you'll receive an email notification.

### A Few Requests

We've found that roof rake sections make wonderful flagpoles and banner poles. If you have a roof rake (or 10’-15’ light metal poles or conduit) to contribute, we'll be happy to take it off your hands!

Donations...we've purchased banners and grommets and flags and zip ties and bungee cords, and we'll be getting more. We’ve purchased 20” x 30” letter boards for messaging we can change. All this costs $$$. We'll have a bucket for donations, and if you could throw something in, that'd be great. And if not, that's perfectly OK, too - your presence is what's really important. See where the money's going! https://tinyurl.com/IN-SLWMProtestTeamFinancials

title: Hands Across Chicagoland
description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens as we form a human chain of conscience across Chicagoland in peaceful protest against Trump’s illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defend the Constitution.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street and California Ave to Douglass Park. This is a peaceful protest. We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

Find and reserve your spot here: www.handsacrosschi.com

Using the website widget will help us spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people close to where they live.

President Trump has defied court orders and forcibly sent people to a torture dungeon in El Salvador without a hearing or due process. Now he claims he’s unable to bring them back. He's ignored court rulings and arrested judges. If he can do this to them, he can do it to anyone.

These are the actions of a dictator—not a democratically elected president. Silence is not an option. When leaders cross the line into authoritarianism, it’s up to us—the people—to push back. This protest is about more than politics. It's about defending basic human dignity, civil liberties, and the idea that no one is above the law.

title: Stefanik Picnic Protest: Say NO to Stefanik & the GOP!
description:
Join Capital Region Indivisible groups and other area activists to protest Elise Stefanik and the GOP at their Spring Picnic in Elm Avenue Park, Bethlehem. 

ARRIVAL TIME: Plan to be parked and in place by 1:30 when GOP will start arriving. Their event starts at 2:00 and people will arrive before that. Also press often come early and then leave, so we want good numbers early.

PARKING: As you enter the park, the best place to park are the lots on your right behind the tennis courts. If those fill up head to the left and park in the large lots next to the pool complex. Do NOT park by the playground further down. 

WHERE WE WILL BE LOCATED: We will be protesting along the road on Rt. 32 and immediately inside the park along the road leading to the parking lots. We are not protesting at the event pavilion as we want to keep this peaceful, AND optics for newspaper pictures will be a lot better with us all at the front of the park.

MESSAGING AND SIGNS: Let's be sure everyone knows the harms the GOP and Stefanik are inflicting on everyday people by their votes to cut benefits and programs (Medicaid, food stamps, rental assistance, benefits for children with disabilities, etc) all so they can give tax breaks for their wealthy donors, corporations and billionaire friends, that Stefanik votes in lock step with the Republican led Congress, and that she is not welcome here!

HANDS OFF ________________ GOP!
HANDS OFF OUR HEALTHCARE ELISE!
GO HOME ELISE!
ELISE & GOP VOTE FOR TAX CUTS FOR BILLIONAIRES!
NO CUTS TO OUR BENEFITS FOR BILLIONAIRE GIVE AWAYS!
SHAME ON THE GOP!
ELISE, YOU ARE NOT WELCOME HERE!

SAFETY AND RESTROOMS: We will have trained Safety marshalls circulating and helping to direct you to parking and restrooms. Restrooms are in the warming hut if you are familiar with the park.

Everyone must be committed to non-violence and non-engagement even if provoked. We want a peaceful and powerful demonstration.

description:

title: Protect The Constitution - Protest on The Norwalk Town Green
description:
Join us Saturday, May 31st @2PM on the Historic Norwalk Green for a peaceful sign-waving protest to protect the constitution! Our constitutional rights are under attack and we need to keep the pressure up. Stand up! Fight back!

Hands off our rights! Hands off our people! Hands off free speech! Hands off LGBTQ+ rights! Hands off due process! Hands off union and workers! Hands off working families! Hands off Medicaid/Medicare! Hands off education! Hands off diversity, equity and inclusion! 

During this event, there will be a public reading of the Constitution by members of the public and invited speakers. Please RSVP for more information.

Thanks!

TRANSPORTATION AND PARKING:

Parking near The Green is limited, so you may prefer to walk or take transit. If you can, consider public transit:

East Norwalk Metro North station is a 20-minute walk to the Town Green.

Norwalk Transit District runs frequent bus service from the Greater Norwalk area to Burnell Blvd, a short walk from the Town Green:

- From Flax Hill or Hospital Hill, take the WHEELs 9 on Fairfield Ave or 
   Stevens St.
- From East Norwalk, take the WHEELs 11 from Van Zant Street or East Ave,
   or the WHEELs 7 from Westport Ave or Strawberry Hill Ave.
- From Merritt 7 or Main Ave area, take the WHEELs 3 on Main Ave or 
  Glover Ave.
- From other parts of Norwalk, you can take Wheels2U 
  (https://www.wheels2u.org/) starting at 1 PM.


Parking: 

Please park at either:
Yankee Doodle Garage, Norwalk
or Norwalk City Hall

Both of these are a 10-15 minute walk to the Green.

Please only park on the side streets near the Town Green if you have an accessible parking permit! We're trying to keep the protest as inclusive as we can!

Please email goodtroublenorwalk@gmail.com for additional accessibility information.

title: "MAMA SAID: RISE UP" Santa Clarita, CA - 💐 MOM'S DAY💐(Indivisible CA27) SCV
description:
This Mother’s Day, we gather not just with flowers—but with fire in our hearts and justice in our voices. On Saturday, May 10, we rally in honor of all mothers:
🌸 The ones who raised us in freedom,
🌸 The ones who are raising the next generation,
🌸 The ones who dream of becoming moms someday—and deserve the right to choose when and if they do,
🌸 And the mothers enduring the fallout of failed policies: economic hardship, crumbling healthcare systems, attacks on reproductive freedom, and schools stripped of resources.

This is also for the mothers of immigrants, of children wrongfully detained, and of communities silenced by cruelty and neglect. It’s for every woman fighting to give her children a better future—and for the daughters who are demanding one.

🚨On Saturday, May 10 from 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM, we’ll be at Good Trouble Corner (McBean & Valencia Blvd, Santa Clarita) to stand together in solidarity.🚨

We’re not waiting for change. We are the change. We’re building a movement where every voice counts and every family matters.

A core principle behind this event is a commitment to nonviolence and community care. We expect all participants to uplift each other and de-escalate when needed—we lead with peace, love, and strength. We recommend all participants review our safety and security resource before your event: https://indivisi.org/safety

💌 More Info: www.indivisibleCA27.com
📧 Contact Us: CA27indivisible@gmail.com

Bring your signs. Bring your stories. Bring your love for the women who made you. ✊💐
Let’s show up for all our mothers—past, present, and future.
accessibility_notes:
There is parking in the Valencia Mall.  Please do not park in the Facey Medical Corner, we reserve that for people who will visit the facility.  Please remember to stay of the street and be silent when we hear ambulance or firemen sirens.  Let's keep the space clean, and give space and assistance for people with special needs.   
Thank you.

title: Tesla Takedown - Stanford Mall
description:
CALSTRS and CALPERS: Divest from Tesla Funds NOW!

City of Palo Alto: Divest from Tesla Funds NOW!

STOP THE BILLIONAIRE TAKEOVER. WE ARE THE MANY. THEY ARE THE FEW. JOIN US.

We know making lots of noise is typically part of a good protest. But most protests aren’t right across the street from a Ronald McDonald House. Let’s take care to keep our noise levels down to a dull roar. Bring your energy and spirit, but let’s ditch the cowbells, drums and car honks. We can get our point across without interfering with our neighbors on the other side of the road.

This is a peaceful demonstration, and any conflicts or altercations will not be tolerated. Walk away if one arises and report it to the demonstration leader on site if it is a serious altercation. We will comply with requests from the police, including if we are asked to leave.

Do not boo or confront Tesla drivers or cars, or Tesla employees. Remember that most Tesla drivers are our allies, and many are protesting with us!

No one voted for Musk. Join the peaceful Tesla Takedown movement!

In solidarity, please add #LatinoFreeze or #LatinoFreezeMovement to placards.

Free Ulises, Free Kilmar, Free Khalil. Free them all! 

Elon Musk is destroying our democracy, and he's using the fortune he built at Tesla to do it. We are taking nonviolent action at Tesla to stop Musk's illegal coup.

⚡Sell your Teslas, dump your stock, join the picket lines.

⚡ We're tanking Tesla's stock price to stop Musk.

⚡Stopping Musk will help save lives and protect our democracy.

The stakes couldn’t be higher. No one is coming to save us. Not politicians, not the media, not the courts.

Tesla Takedown is a peaceful protest movement. We oppose violence, vandalism and destruction of property. This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly.

#TeslaTakedown #BoycottTesla #DueProcess #LatinoFreeze

We practice peaceful nonviolence and nonconfrontation. Although we are all very concerned about Elon Musk's activities and unconstitutional meddling in our democracy, we protest peacefully. Do not respond to those who may express a different point of view. And please do not target people passing by in Tesla vehicles. Our focus is on supporting democracy and opposing the destruction of our institutions, the agencies that we depend on, our rights, and our freedoms.

Let's keep the rally momentum going! Stand up for democracy! Build community! Bring your signs and your voices! Bring friends!

title: Protest @ Tesla Lyndhurst on Thursday, May 8th, 11:30 AM - 1:30 PM
description:
There have been protests at the Tesla Store every Saturday since the middle of February.  Attendance has been outstanding in spite of some adverse weather conditions.  And support from passing motorists has been truly amazing.  

But Trump and Musk continue to destroy our democratic freedoms and carelessly dismantle our government institutions.  So let's turn up the heat with additional protests on weekdays!  Thursday through the lunch period appears to be the next most popular time other than Saturday.  Let's protest from 11:30 to 1:30 and see what kind of impact we have.  Consider it a test case and if the results are good, we will probably continue.

Rules & Reminders: Bring a sign. Stay on the sidewalk & allow pedestrians to pass. Do not jaywalk across Mayfield Road (police will be watching). Use the crosswalk just west of Tesla. Don't block driveway entrances or exits. Don't harass Tesla customers or employees. Do not argue with counter protesters. Do not use inflammatory language or make threats. Watch for peacekeepers in yellow vests and immediately report any disturbances to them. Follow any instructions from Lyndhurst Police. PROTEST PEACEFULLY.

Parking is available at Messiah Lutheran Church, 5200 Mayfield Road. Please be respectful and park on the EAST SIDE of the lot first (away from the Tesla Store). Additional parking is available at the Lyndhurst Community of Faith Church, 5312 Mayfield Road. Please enter the EAST DRIVEWAY as the west driveway is exit only.

title: Press Conference Block Party
description:
VENMO @SaveFWCC to contribute to our campaign

FOLLOW on Instagram @SaveFWCC

For over a century, Fort Washington Collegiate Church has served the uptown community as more than just a house of worship. Ft. Washington is a beacon of light, a collective gathering point, and an anchor for numerous programs serving our Washington Heights and uptown community. The closure on June 30, 2025, will force Ft. Washington and the programs that call this place home to shutter their doors, leaving a massive void in our communal social fabric. 

Ft. Washington is a symbol of unity and togetherness. It is a center for local music and the arts through the Fort Washington Community Choir, Washington Heights Chamber Orchestra, Up Theater, and Uptown Enclave. It embodies interfaith connection through the Fort Tryon Jewish Center, offers a sanctuary of nature and beauty through the Fort Washington Green, a center for recovery through AA, Al-Anon, and NA meetings, and nourishes families through the Fort Fridge.

The greater Collegiate Board’s recent decision to close Ft. Washington will rob our community of these essential programs, resources, and vital communal space. As friends and neighbors who benefit from and greatly appreciate Ft. Washington's contributions to our community, we seek your help. We implore the Collegiate Board to stop the proposed shutdown on June 30, 2025 and allow Ft. Washington and its community partners time to secure additional funding.

The closure of Ft. Washington’s campus represents the death of a piece of the heart of our uptown community. The fight to keep this beloved space open is a fight to keep our community whole. Please join this community led effort to urge the Consistory to stop the proposed closure of Ft. Washington Collegiate Church on June 30, 2025. 

Some of the groups who meet in this sacred space include:
Support and Recovery Groups
Fort Fridge
Fort Tryon Jewish Center
Fort Washington Collegiate Church
Fort Washington Community Choir
Fort Washington Green
Uptown Enclave
Up Theater Company
Washington Heights Chamber Orchestra

_________________________


Durante más de un siglo, la Iglesia Colegiada de Fort Washington ha servido a la comunidad del norte de Manhattan como algo más que un lugar de adoración. Fort Washington es un faro de luz, un punto de encuentro colectivo y un pilar para numerosos programas que sirven a nuestra comunidad de Washington Heights.Cerrando las puertas de Fort Washington el 30 de junio de 2025 dejará un enorme vacío en el tejido social de nuestra comunidad.

Fort Washington es un símbolo de unidad y solidaridad. Es un centro para la música local y las artes a través del Coro Comunitario de Fort Washington, la Orquesta de Cámara de Washington Heights, Up Theater y Uptown Enclave. Representa la conexión interreligiosa mediante el Centro Judío Fort Tryon, ofrece un santuario de naturaleza y belleza a través del Fort Washington Green, un centro de recuperación con los grupos de apoyo AA, Al-Anon, y NA, y nutre a las familias a través del Fort Fridge.

La reciente decisión del Consistorio de cerrar Fort Washington privará a nuestra comunidad de estos programas esenciales, recursos y espacio comunitario. Como amigos y vecinos que benefician y aprecian profundamente las contribuciones de Fort Washington a nuestra comunidad, solicitamos su ayuda. Imploramos al Consistorio que detenga el cierre propuesto para el 30 de junio de 2025 y permita que Fort Washington y sus socios comunitarios tengan tiempo para asegurar fondos adicionales.

El cierre del campus de Fort Washington representa la pérdida de una parte del corazón de nuestra comunidad del norte de Manhattan. La lucha por mantener este querido espacio abierto es una lucha por preservar la integridad de nuestra comunidad. Únase a este esfuerzo liderado por la comunidad para detener el cierre propuesto de la Iglesia Colegial Fort Washington el 30 de junio de 2025.

title: RESIST and RECLAIM: Stop The Billionaire Takeover
description:
Our democracy is under attack. The current administration is making a full-blown power grab — shredding the rule of law, ignoring the courts, and handing over control of our country’s financial system to a billionaire crony. This is a hostile takeover, a coup, and we need relentless, united pressure to stop it.

We refuse to let our communities be ruled by greed, racism, and corruption. Here in Mahoning County, we draw the line. We demand justice. We demand a future that puts people before profit. We envision a future where healthcare is a right, not a privilege; where public education is for everyone; where billionaires don’t get to rewrite the rules to favor themselves and enslave the workers. 

This is more than a protest – this is a movement to reclaim our power, restore our rights, and fight for a future where everyone is treated with dignity and respect.

title: Defending Democracy: Woman's Rights
description:
Join us for our 10th consecutive rally to Defend Democracy in beautiful downtown Bethel.  While our overall theme is Defending Democracy, each week we pick a specific focus.  On Saturday May 10th 11am -12:30pm, our focus will be Woman's Rights.

The rally is non-partisian.  All are welcome.  We'll have speakers address the attack on Woman's Rights by threats to DEI, Voting rights and Healthcare.
Guest speakers include a local ACLU lawyer involved in the reproductive rights movement and a local community member who would like to share their story and experience on why women’s healthcare needs to be equally accessible for everyone in this country.  Our live music will be provided by Sweet Polly Duo, a great duo from Clinton, CT.  They are an energetic pairing of vocals by Pat Anwari and guitar by Rocky Ridge.

There will be something for everyone.  We'll have speakers, we'll rally with our signs, we'll take a short march and we'll have live music.  We also like to end each week with a sing-a-long.

A sign-making table will also be available,  complete with all the necessary supplies,  for young and old to make signs for the rally.

We also collect a non-perishable food item for our local food pantry each week.

title: Stop Super Speeders Rally in Memory of Niyell McCrorey
description:
Niyell McCrorey was hit at this intersection by an SUV on October 24th, 2024, shortly before her 14th birthday. After battling for her life at in pediatric intensive care for several days, she succumbed to her injuries and passed away on November 1st from traumatic brain injury, leaving her friends and family devastated

 

In her honor, we will share stories of her beautiful life, and we will call on the New York State Legislature to pass the Stop Super Speeders Bill.

title: Protect NY's Climate Law - Syracuse
description:
Join Citizen Action of NY, PUSH Buffalo, NY Renews, Third Act Upstate New York, and local CNY groups to rally and testify at a DEC public hearing in Syracuse on June 3 at noon to defend NY’s Climate Law.

New Yorkers will join to voice their support for climate leadership and to urge Governor Hochul to stand up to Trump by funding climate legislation. Join us and help make this impactful by emailing egormley@citizenactionny.org.

The climate change-denier in the White House is doing everything he can to eliminate climate progress in this country. We need climate leadership in NY, and we need it now. Unfortunately, in January, Governor Hochul revealed that she’s delaying a crucial component of the state’s Climate Law called Cap and Invest. 


Cap and Invest is an emissions-reduction program that would limit, or cap, emissions from major polluters in the state. That cap would tighten over time, gradually reducing the amount of emissions allowed for release. Meanwhile, major polluters will have to pay to release polluting emissions up to the level of the cap. Those funds from polluters will then be used to invest in green energy, jobs, home decarbonization programs, and similar efforts to support NY communities.

To move Cap and Invest forward, we need the Department of Environmental Conservation (DEC) to release three sets of regulations that hold polluters accountable to Cap and Invest. Unfortunately, Governor Hochul has  released only one.
