title: Roswell Empowered Alive After 5 Sidewalk Protest
description:
We had our first successful rally in Roswell on 5/3–let’s keep up the momentum. Empower Roswell, Ignite Change. This is only the spark!

Roswell may be a small city just outside of Atlanta, but our voices are big. Our voices matter.

It’s important for our leaders—both local and state-wide—to know and understand that people all across this country, this state, this city—the city of Roswell—are not going to accept the reckless agenda of the current administration.

Regardless of political affiliation, we all know that deep down what has been happening is not ok. And we want our leaders—regardless of political affiliation to hold this administration accountable.

We want leaders who will fight for the futures of our families, not those concerned only about their fortunes.

We want leaders who will stand up and fight for our schools and ensure our children have access to quality education, not those who want to erase history and rip away programs designed to help students that need it the most. We want leaders who will protect our neighbors, not those who spread fear and hateful rhetoric and seek to eliminate diversity in our communities.

We want leaders who will fight for our rights, fight for democracy, not those who promote corruption, oligarchy and tyranny.

We want leaders who will protect healthcare including Medicare, Medicaid, and affordable treatment and prescriptions, not those who seek to pull the rug out from the most vulnerable members of our communities—veterans, the elderly, those will special needs, the sick, the impoverished.
We want leaders who lead by example, not those who sell their own Bible, but exemplify the opposite of its contents.

We want our leaders—local and nationwide—to hear us and take action against Trump and his corrupt billionaire buddies. And that action starts here, in Roswell, GA.

A peaceful sidewalk protest on both sides of Atlanta St between Magnolia and Norcross Streets—parallel to the Alive After 5 event on Canton St.

Please remain on the sidewalk, no signs that say “honk”, follow all local laws.

This event will be rain or shine.
Parking gets tight—please make a plan to carpool, park in one of the local churches, or find paid parking (I know that’s not ideal, but make sure if you do park in a paid lot you pay—typically by phone—we don’t want anyone getting towed).

Thank you for your support and look forward to seeing you there!
Roswell Empowered: Empower Roswell, Ignite Change

title: Stand Up / Speak Out Rally in Hudson
description:
Stand Up/Speak Out is holding a rally in Hudson on May 25 in response to the ongoing cuts to the federal workforce and services that support veterans, Social Security beneficiaries, and healthcare providers and patients in New York. The event hopes to encourage local citizens to gather, learn from one another, and sound the alarm that no one is safe in an America that has turned its back on its veterans, the elderly, and the ability of millions to access healthcare. 

Our speaker lineup so far includes Andrea Goldstein, a veteran and a former staffer of the House Committee on Veterans Affairs; Rennie Glasgow, Vice President of the American Federation of Government Employees (AFGE ), Local 3343; and Ashley Fox, MA, PhD, a public policy and global health policy expert. In addition, we will hear from folks directly impacted by the current and anticipated federal cuts to the Veterans Administration, Social Security, and government healthcare programs, including Medicaid.

Come join in! Bring your signs and your friends!

title: Pickerington Stands Up for Democracy!

location.venue: Public sidewalk between Bob Evans and Steak 'n Shake

description:
There are one thousand and one things to be outraged about right now. What has motivated you to say, “Enough!”? Join us for Fairfield County Indivisible’s first Pickerington protest rally. 

WHAT: Rally on 256 

WHEN: Thursday, May 15, from 4:14 - 5:45 pm 

WHERE: On the public sidewalk between Bob Evans and Steak ‘n Shake on Hill Road 

Rally guidelines: 

● Stay safe and stand back from the curb. 

● No vulgar signs or apparel. 

● Remain positive and do not engage with those who do not share our views. 

● Be respectful of local law enforcement. 

● Be respectful of nearby businesses. If you park in their lots, please patronize these businesses.  

We look forward to seeing you at this first, but not last, Pickerington Stands Up for Democracy Rally.

title: Hands Across Chicagoland
description:
Join tens of thousands of your fellow Chicago-area citizens, along with Western Kane Democrats, Dupage Democrats, Batavia Township Democrats, St. Charles Township Democrats, Indivisible Fox Valley Rising, and We Can Lead Change - we will form a human chain of conscience across Chicaoland in peaceful protest against Trump's illegal and authoritarian actions and the GOP's failure to defned the Constitution.

Bring signs, wear black, and make some noise.

We will line sidewalks along 30 miles from Aurora to Chicago along Ogden Ave, 26th Street, and California Ave. to Douglass Park.  This is a peaceful protest.  We will not block streets or businesses along the route.

Please go to www.handsacrosschi.com and enter your zip code to get an assigned location along the route.  This is important so that we can spread people out evenly along the route, while keeping people closer to where they live.

title: CD 3 - KILEY - Save Mercy Hospital from Medicaid Cuts!
description:
The Republican led Congress is proposing to make devastating cuts to healthcare programs which could impact 15 million Californians, including children and people with disabilities!  And they're making the cuts to give huge tax breaks to millionaires and billionaires.

Many hospitals around the state could lose major funding. Mercy Hospital could lose millions of dollars.  The proposed cuts would mean devastating cutbacks in services and longer wait times - even for people who have private insurance.  

To stop the cuts and save lives we need to get a handful of Republican Congressmembers to vote NO on the proposed healthcare cuts.  We'll be rallying to save Mercy Hospital in Folsom on Tuesday, May 13th at 11:30 AM with doctors, nurses, other healthcare providers and community supporters to call on Congressman Kevin Kiley to vote NO on any cuts to Medicaid!

title: Indivisible TX-24 Saturday Tesla #MuskorUs Protest __ Southlake
description:
Continuing on each Saturday weekly protest! 

Things are getting worse for us. Keep showing up to make it even worse for Elon!!

Take Peaceful Protest Action at Tesla showrooms everywhere, including Southlake.

Stopping Musk will help save jobs, lives and our democracy.

The stakes couldn’t be higher. No one is coming to save us—not politicians, not the media. So take pictures use #TeslaTakedown #MuskOrUs Your courage is contagious. Showing up builds community and constituent power. 

Important Guidelines
Public Space Only: Stay on sidewalks and public areas—do not block business entrances or trespass on private property. Please follow all state and local regulations regarding gathering on public and private property.
Stay on Message: This is about Musk’s political takeover, not Tesla, SpaceX, or X as companies.
Indivisible is focused on Musk’s role in the Trump-Musk coup. 
Indivisible is not advising and does not condone any actions that directly interfere with the daily operations or activities of any business or entity. Please follow all state and local guidelines regarding gathering on public or private business property. 
A core principle behind all Musk or Us events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values, and to act lawfully at these events. Weapons of any kind, including those legally permitted, should not be brought to events.

Join Indivisible TX-24 and allies. Be Peaceful. Take pics and video
#muskorus #nokings

We have **NO KINGS** here in America. And, _*we won't tolerate*_ a president who acts like one. So, join us at Alameda City Hall on Saturday June 14th from 12 noon till 1 PM to make our voices heard.

Also, we will have a food donation bin at the protest site in support of our neighbors in need. Please bring non-perishable food items for donation. Every little bit helps! Look for more details to be included in upcoming email updates to registered attendees.

Your presence will be appreciated by everyone! Thanks in advance.
accessibility_notes: This event location is the public plaza in front of Alameda City Hall. The plaza is a flat, paved area. There are a few benches at the location, but if you cannot stand for the duration of your time at the protest, you are welcome to bring a lawn chair or camp chair. Just make sure to set your chair up in an area off to the side, not in the middle, for safety reasons. There is an adjacent bus stop. The closest bathroom facilities are located at the Alameda Free Library at 1550 Oak St (a block away on an adjacent street). Parking will be scarce. Please use ride-sharing or public transit.

title: No Kings
description:
Indivisible: Heart of the Ozarks will be joining the National Day of Protest to declare on Flag Day that we don't want a King. 

Trump is planning a multi-million dollar Military Parade for his birthday on June 14th. We must show how disrespectful this is to the Military and every US Citizen. No King - No Dictator

Bring a Friend or two. We have to keep the momentum going.
I will bring blank poster board and markers to make your own signs if needed. Please no foul language and keep the message to the issues.

All Rallies will be held in West Plains Missouri at the corner of Hwy 63 and 160 near Ruby Tuesday.

Be safe and stay back from the curb. Do not block the sight lines for cars turning off 63 onto 160.
Do not take up the parking places for any of the businesses. In fact, if you can be a customer that would be great.
Do not engage with anyone looking for trouble. If there is any outside trouble, do your best to de-escalate, and if necessary please dial 911. The West Plains Police know we will be there.

title: Join DeKalb Dems at Juneteenth in Stonecrest
description:
The City of Stonecrest is celebrating Juneteenth bigger than ever before this year by hosting it's 3rd annual Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom on Saturday June 14, 2025.

DeKalb Dems will have a visibility tent and we need volunteers to assist with set up and act as Ambassadors who listen to citizen's concerns, offer ways we can support them, and talk about what they can do to safeguard our freedom.

Juneteenth commemorates the effective end of slavery in the United States. Two years after President Lincoln signed the Emancipation Proclamation, news reached Texas and, upon learning they were free, former slaves immediately began celebrating with prayer, feasting, song, and dance. The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will celebrate African American culture, heritage, and, most importantly, abolishment of slavery.

The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will feature an expanded kidz zone, live performances, food trucks, vendors, and fireworks show. It is a place for all races, nationalities, and religions to join hands and truthfully acknowledge a period in history that shaped and continues to influence our society today, according to a news release. This event is free and open to the public, and we encourage everyone to attend and learn more about the history and culture of Juneteenth!

Please sign up for a shift below and be a part of this Celebration of Freedom.

title: Rally for Democracy and Free Speech at Farmers Market
description:
Defend Free Speech by exercising it!  This is opening day of the Burlington Farmers Market and we'll be along Pine Street with signs reminding folks what is at stake right now. We're standing up for democracy, standing up for the Constitution, and standing against the Trump Administration's chaos and lawlessness.

Bring signs, musical instruments, and whatever else might cheer us on.

ALSO -> We're doing a poster party on Thursday 5/8 to prepare for upcoming rallies. Join us at Queen City Brewery event room, from 2-4pm. Bring supplies and good cheer. Great beers from our hosts at the Brewery in back.  703 Pine Street.

title: Stand Up for Justice* Equity * Democracy Rally and Food Drive

location.venue: Castillo de San Marcos National Monument

description:
We are standing up to protest the Trump administration for:
-Defying and intimidating our justices and legal system!
-Treating people like rodents to be eliminated, Taking their personal belongings including their cash, trashing their homes, locking them up without due process, shipping them out of the country 
-Trashing the rights of our LGBTQ+ community
-Slashing jobs that are vital to the welfare of our country
-Slashing federal jobs; Veterans fill 1/3 of all federal jobs
-And as everyone says: Too Many Things to List Here!!

We will also be having a Food Drive to help our local community! 
Bring:     non-perishable foods, canned items (pop-tops where possible)
              pasta, dry cereals, rice, Spam, peanut butter, jelly, dry milk, 
              powdered drink mix, dried herbs, spices, granola bars, fruit cups

We will be dropping off your donations at local food pantries. 

We do have signs and flags available for you to use at the rally at our Dem Party table; we just ask that you return them so we can use at the next rally! 

Look forward to seeing everyone there!    
If you would like to help out at future rallies; please stop by the Dem tent and let us know!  We would love to have more volunteers!


A core principle behind all our rallies is a commitment to peaceful, respectful action. We have safety people available to answer any questions and we expect everyone to avoid any eye, verbal contact, or physical contact with counter protestors.  Do Not Give Them the Satisfaction!  
THANK YOU!

title: NO KINGS Raleigh
description:
This June 14th, stand with us at the steps of the North Carolina State Capitol for No Kings Day—a nonpartisan, peaceful rally in defense of the American principles we all hold dear: democracy, accountability, and the rule of law.

Across the political spectrum, more and more Americans are feeling disillusioned by leaders who put themselves above the people. This day is for anyone who believes that no one—no matter how powerful—should be treated like royalty in a nation built on liberty.

We’re gathering not in anger, but in unity. This is a space for reflection, connection, and a shared commitment to a country where leaders serve, not rule. Whether you're conservative, progressive, independent, or politically unsure—if you believe in the idea of a government by and for the people, this rally is for you.

This is a peaceful, de-escalation-focused event. There is no place here for violence, intimidation, or hate. We welcome calm, respectful voices who want to help shape a future rooted in mutual respect and civic responsibility.

Bring your signs, your friends, your conscience—and your belief that the United States was never meant to have kings.

title: No Kings On D-Day
description:
# On June 6th, 2025, the Anniversary of D-Day, Mass 50501 will hold an event in remembrance of our heroes in uniform, past and present.

Our mission is the preservation of the democracy that they fought—and in some cases died—to protect on the shores of Europe. We will feature speakers who are themselves veterans, who will speak on history, duty, honor, sacrifice, and patriotism. We will conduct a wreath-laying ceremony at the Soldiers and Sailors Monument on the Boston Common featuring patriotic renditions of “Taps,” “Battle Hymn of the Republic,” and other songs. We will protest cuts to the VA, oppose the undemocratic way in which the administration has treated its duties, reaffirm our support for our allies, and recommit ourselves to the principles that have governed the nation and its military for centuries, and we will remind the people that veterans and active duty military personnel exist to protect the nation against all enemies, foreign and domestic. It will be both a protest and a solemn event of remembrance. 

## Event Program

## Act 1: Invocation of Service
An honor guard procession will bear American, State, and Service flags from the Soldiers and Sailors Monument to the stage, followed by an invocation and remarks from the Program Director. 

## Act 2: The Citizen Soldier
We'll hear from ordinary citizens—veterans and those who support them—addressing the issues that matter to veterans today.

## Act 3: A Call to Duty
VIP speakers will offer stories to help draw us together, and remind us that the bonds of service do not end upon separation from the military and that participation in our democracy is essential to its health and prosperity.

## Act 4: Honor the Fallen
The honor guard and key speakers will process back to the Soldiers and Sailors Monument to lay a wreath, followed by Taps, a moment of silence, and closing words. 

# Flags are welcome, but please leave protest signs at home.

title: Kick Out the Clowns
description:
Placer Women Democrats are joining The Women's March for the June 14 Rally!

When you elect clowns, they don’t become leaders. The country becomes a circus. 🤡

On June 14, Donald Trump will honor himself with a four-mile military parade in our nation’s capitol. Trump’s tacky parade was inspired by dictators he idolizes, and will cost taxpayers nearly $100 million. 

Organizer and strategist Daniel Hunter has written that “Humor is important for our psyches — and to take fascists down a notch[…] Humor is key for morale and exposing the vulnerability of the strongman image.” This is where the ridiculous meets the resistance—and where the future is on the line.

June 14 is our chance to reflect the absurdity of the MAGA regime and the clowns who lead it. To meet this moment, Women’s March will host community circuses nationwide—bold, creative actions that mirror the chaos MAGA has sown across the country. Together, we’ll set a national record for the most circuses held in a single day while we simultaneously refuse to celebrate a petty clown who desperately wants to be seen as strong. We won’t stop until we build the country we all deserve.
`
Our grassroots street circuses turn satire into resistance and reclaim the big tent for democracy.

#KickOutTheClowns
#GreatestShitshowOnEarth
#CommunitiesNotClowns
#ClownsAgainstClowns 
#BigTentResistance

title: No Cake for False Kings
description:
🗓️ June 14, 2025
🕐 1:00–4:00 PM
📍 17th Street NW Bridge, over Atlanta highways (near Atlantic Station)

On June 14th, while Donald Trump attempts to display military power meant to silence dissent, we will rise above the noise—literally and symbolically.

No Cake for False Kings is a high-visibility, nonviolent protest that will take place on the 17th Street NW pedestrian bridge, which crosses over ALL of Atlanta’s busiest highways. We are joining activists across America to send one unified message: we reject authoritarianism, abuse of power, and the erasure of our rights.

This is not a celebration. This is a warning.
There will be no cake, no crowns, and no complicity.

🔥 What to Expect:
- A powerful visual presence over the highway with large protest banners

- Protesters lining both sides of the bridge sidewalks to reach drivers below and pedestrians around

- Organized chants, signs, and nonviolent resistance

- An Information & Resource Table with know-your-rights guides, activist materials, and ways to plug in

- A Water & Cooling Station to ensure safety in the heat

** Participants are strongly encouraged to WEAR RED as a unified symbol of protest and defiance. 

🎒What to bring: 
- For those wanting to avoid the summer sun, having an umbrella to provide shade is encouraged. 

- Wear a hat, sunglasses, and sunscreen to protect from the sun!

- Water, water, water! We will have a water station as well as cooling towels and packs, but these are limited, so bring water for yourself and your group if possible.

- Signs and flags are strongly encouraged, but organizers will have extras for those in need *limited, first come first serve 

- Foldable chair: for those needing a break from standing for long periods of time

-Snacks: protesting takes energy, so bring some snacks to refuel! 


🧭 Getting There:
-Parking is available at Atlantic Station just steps away from the bridge

- For those using public transit, MARTA’s Arts Center Station is the closest stop and offers a shuttle to Atlantic Station

This protest is about visibility and truth. We must be loud, proud, and impossible to ignore. Bring your voice, your signs, and your conviction.

Together, we will show this country that we do not bow to tyrants—we rise up against them.

title: Hands Off Medicaid Rally!
description:
Drastic cuts to the federal budget are underway and we are standing up to say:

Hands Off Medicaid!

1.2 million Minnesotans rely on Medicaid (aka Medical Assistance) in some way. Proposed cuts to Medicaid are estimated to cost Minnesotans up to $1.6 Billion per year in federal funds.

AFSCME Local 34 workers provide social services to the residents of Hennepin County, many of whom rely on Medicaid. We stand firmly against any cuts to healthcare benefits for our residents or anyone else for that matter.

We cannot afford cuts to Medicaid - join us at the Paul D Wellstone Federal Building on Tuesday, May 13th at 12pm and make your voice heard!
accessibility_notes: This event will take place outside the building on the sidewalk, this building is open to the public for restroom use.

title: #NoKings Day with Sister District Project SF
description:
Join your friends and neighbors at Sister District Project San Francisco for the #NoKings mass protest and day of defiance!

On June 14, rise up with millions across the country, on Tr*mp's planned military parade day, to stand in opposition and fight back against the attacks on our freedoms by this jury-determined rapist, twice-impeached, 34-time convicted felon, and January 6 traitor. 

Look for the Sister District San Francisco banner in front of 350 McAllister between Larkin & Polk from 10:30 – 11am before we head to the main rally in front of City Hall. 

Bring signs, wear your SDP t-shirt and caps if you have them (we'll have a few extras). 

Together, let's demand a country that puts our families over billionaires' fortunes—public schools over private profits, healthcare over hedge funds, prosperity over the profits of price-gouging and climate polluting corporations.

_A core principle behind all #NoKings events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values._

To learn more about this national day of action, visit [nokings.org](https://www.nokings.org/)

To learn more about Sister District Project, visit [SisterDistrict.com](https://sisterdistrict.com/strategy).

Since 2016, Sister District Project has been building enduring progressive power in the states to improve people's lives, including by supporting community-based organizations led by people of color on the ground, like [New Virginia Majority](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/sd016-va-nvmef-sf), who do critical grassroots work year round.

You are welcome to join any of our monthly meetings, whichever is most convenient for you! 

We host events on **Zoom the first Tuesday** of each month; in-person **Happy Hours on the first Thursdays** of even-numbered months; in-person **Coffee Hours on first Thursdays** of odd-numbered months (locations vary); or in-person **Postcard events** on third Sundays or Mondays.

title: Croton, NY: Pass a Resolution Against Project Maple
description:
**Join us outside the Croton Board of Trustees meeting to demand local action against Project Maple** — a dangerous fracked gas pipeline expansion plan that threatens our climate, our river, and our health.

Fossil Fuel company Enbridge's Project Maple would expand the amount of fracked gas running through the existing Algonquin Pipeline (which runs through Westchester County) by replacing existing pipe and expanding compressor stations. 

This project would lock us into decades of fossil fuel dependence — just when we need to be transitioning to clean energy. It’s risky, unnecessary, and completely out of step with New York’s climate goals. **Croton has the chance to be a climate leader by passing a resolution opposing this reckless project.**

📣 **Join us outside Croton-on-Hudson Village Hall, where we’ll rally together, then head into the board meeting to make powerful public comments demanding the Village take a stand.**

Let’s pack the room and show our elected officials that Croton stands for climate justice, not fossil fuel expansion. Bring your friends, your voice, and your passion — we’ll have talking points and signs ready to go!

title: Mondays @ McCormick's
description:
This is an EMERGENCY! Senate Protest Event in Philadelphia Continues This Week and For the Foreseeable Future.

Now called "Monday's at McCormick's" each Monday at noon - rain or shine - Here's why:

We are living in a MAGA-republican Coup. We were warned. Now it's here!

Here at home our democratic rights are being eroded and the Trump/Musk team is putting us all in danger. The limits of Executive power against the courts are being tested every day. If Trump decides to ignore the courts, there is very little they can do to enforce their decisions and unless Congress acts, it would be a true constitutional crisis. (And so far, Congress is controlled by the MAGA movement and the Democrats have not done enough to stand up and fight back.) It could even spiral down into outright civil war as competing factions and states careen between untested solutions to protect their own interests and those of their constituents and funders. There is real harm being done across the entire domestic sector. Layoffs, program cuts for the needy and for the average US resident, persecution of law abiding immigrants and students and other activists for simply speaking their mind and organizing constitutionally protected protest. Fear is also their weapon.

Our international role is being flipped on its head - yes, the US has always had a questionable foreign policy, providing aid and promoting democracy and human rights - to a degree - on the one hand, while at the same time invading other countries for the good of corporate profits and geopolitical dominance. Trump considers a policy to outright invade counties like Mexico and Greenland in violation of international law and to extend US power - A clear expression of Empire! Trump is considering power grabs not unlike those that the Nazi regime in Germany perpetrated in search of "Lebensraum", (Living Space) a euphemism for territorial conquest. And they got away with it (for a while) because the people who stood up were either jailed, exiled or murdered. The rest were either regime supporters (Like the solid 30% base of the MAGA movement) or went along out of fear of retribution. We cannot let fear prevent us from standing up this time. History will judge us.

We now have a true oligarchy in the US and we must fight back!

The Trump administration’s illegal actions and relentless efforts to dismantle protections for vulnerable communities — both here in the U.S. and abroad— have made clear we are in the midst of an authoritarian takeover not unlike what has happened in Orban’s Hungary. 

His plan to "Own Gaza" and move out Palestinians is NOT a plan to destroy Hamas and increase Israeli security - it is ETHNIC CLEANSING pure and simple. It's a land grab. All for development rights and to secure a seaport access to natural gas deposits off the shore of Gaza in the Mediterranean Sea. The Levant gas field includes the shores of historic Palestine (Israel and Gaza), Syria, Lebanon and, on the opposite side, the island of Cyprus. This field is estimated to contain about 122 trillion cubic feet of natural gas. So it will accelerate the climate emergency. 

As we all know Trump/Musk plan to get rid of a number of government agencies that protect our health, livelihood and constitutional rights. - the EPA is on the hit list. The Department of Education is too. So, is the CDC, the NIH and many other important agencies that protect the US public.

As we all know - thousands have already been fired, causing chaos and havoc and real harm to both dedicated civil servants AND people served by life affirming programs voted on by the U.S. people and enacted, in most cases, by the U.S. Congress. The Administration may have authority to make staffing decisions, but as is the case with the Department of Education - many of these agencies can only be eliminated by acts of Congress - Trump has overstepped his legal authority.

Thankfully, the courts have, so far, acted as a check on much of Trumps clear and blatant abuses of executive power. But we cannot count on the courts, particularly the US Supreme court, which has been stacked by Trump appointees and ideologues friendly to executive power. 

Resistance is NOT futile - it is essential. 

We are launching "Monday's at McCormick's" each Monday at noon - rain or shine - we will assemble peaceably - as is our constitutional right - outside Senator McCormick's Philadelphia office until Senator McCormick agrees to meet with us and support our demands: (These will change as conditions develop)

 1 - Stop voting for legislation inspired by Trump's project 2025 agenda - a plan to slash Medicaid, gut school lunch programs, and shut down nursing homes while handing more power to billionaires like Elon Musk. 

2- Roll back Trump's mean spirited and Unconstitutional funding pauses. Shutting down USAID is already killing people in need all over the World. Cuts to programs here in the US could do the same. Funding for these programs are up to the Congress and the US people to decide, not Trump! 

That's just for starters. Overall we want Senator McCormick to represent us all, not just his rich friends. We want Senator McCormick to DO HIS JOB!
The stakes could not be higher. The administration is pushing an authoritarian agenda that threatens our democracy, our rights, and the well-being of millions here at home and around the planet. 

We have the power to resist—and we must use every tool at our disposal to stop them.

title: People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn’t Rule America
description:
## **People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn’t Rule America**

The United States is not a corporation, and our government is not a for-profit enterprise. Elon Musk is not a government official. He’s a billionaire with no accountability to the American people, and nobody voted for him. Our democracy deserves better.

Musk and Trump will only be defeated by a massive, bipartisan movement of everyday Americans standing up against corruption, authoritarianism, and huge tax breaks for the rich, while fighting for the programs that working people need.

** This is a BIPARTISAN, PEACEFUL Protest** 
**No violence or Destruction of Property will be tolerated** 

**The People over Profit Movement**

Right now, millions of Americans across the political divide are struggling. 60% live paycheck to paycheck, many earn very low wages, and 85 million lack proper health insurance. College is too expensive for young people, a quarter of seniors live on $15,000 a year or less, and childhood poverty is among the highest in the world. We also face a severe shortage of affordable housing.

At the same time, the wealthiest Americans, like Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, and Mark Zuckerberg, are getting richer. Since Trump’s election, their combined wealth has grown by over $200 billion—more than the bottom half of the country. Meanwhile, the middle class shrinks, and democracy is at risk.

Our goal is to protect democracy and create an economy that works for everyone, not just the rich. As the wealthiest country in the world, we have the potential to use new technologies to improve everyone’s lives, but instead, most of the wealth goes to the people who need it the least.

We must make healthcare a human right, raise wages to a living standard, improve public education, address the housing crisis, create good-paying jobs to fight climate change, and end all forms of discrimination.

**We the People believe that in the richest country in the history of the world we must establish that:**

1. Healthcare is a human right and must be available to all regardless of income.

2. Every worker in America is entitled to earn a decent income. We must raise the minimum wage to a living wage and make it easier for workers to join unions.

3. We must have the best public educational system in the world, from childcare to vocational training, to graduate school – available to all.

4. We must address the housing crisis and build the millions of units of low-income and affordable housing that we desperately need.

5. We must create millions of good paying jobs as we lead the world in combating the existential threat of climate change.

6. We must abolish all forms of bigotry.

We want people to understand: you can choose Musk or you can choose democracy.

This is a nonviolent event. You are each responsible for your own behavior. This is no different from if you were here today to shop. Stay within your rights, don’t break laws, stay safe, stay peaceful, and avoid any risk you don’t feel comfortable with. Don’t obstruct traffic, protest inside any business, impede people from entering or exiting any property, or commit any acts of property damage. We urge you to ignore counter protestors and stay focused on peacefully delivering our message. If you need help or see something troubling, tell a uniformed police officer or call 911. title: Join the National Day of Action for Single Payer Healthcare!
description:
## It’s time to end the health care crisis. Join the National Day of Action for Single Payer! Saturday, May 31st 1pm-3pm.

Our health care system is broken—and it’s **killing** us. For-profit insurers and corporate middlemen deny care, drive up costs, and profit off our pain. Decades of piecemeal reforms have only made things worse: skyrocketing prices, massive waste, and some of the worst health outcomes among wealthy countries.

**We say: enough.**

### We demand a system that puts people before profit—where health care is treated as a human right, not a business.

#### We are calling for:

- The elimination of private insurance companies and for-profit care.

- A national, publicly funded single payer program that covers everyone—comprehensively and equitably.

- A transformation of our health care system to serve communities, not corporations—freeing caregivers from corporate control and putting power in the hands of the people.

This event is happening in Portland, but we’re not stopping here. Activists are organizing sister actions across Oregon—from the coast to the high desert. Stay tuned for more info on how to plug in near you!

On the **National Day of Action**, people across the country—patients, nurses, union members, small business owners, neighbors and organizers—will take to the streets to demand real change. This is about building a mass movement to take profit out of care and put National Single Payer on the political agenda—now.

Bring your families (kid friendly!), neighbors, friends, everyone you know and join us to turn collective outrage into collective action: put National Single Payer on the nation’s agenda!

title: Stand Up, Superior! - A Tesla/Trump Takedown
description:
Come join us on Saturdays from 11am to 2pm to peacefully protest the corruption and hatred coming from the head of our government currently. 

This will be an on-going event until the madness stops, and unfortunately, it seems as though we might be doing this for a while.
Just to be clear, signing up does not mean you are required to be at every protest. 

The sole purpose of this website is to let you know that people will be there on McCaslin Blvd. every Saturday until we are heard and changes are made.

For your mental and physical health, I recommend taking the occasional Saturday off! Know that others are there keeping the event going strong.

There may be individuals who approach on foot and try to provoke us. 
It is my hope that you’ll be able to ignore them and redirect your attention to the individuals standing beside you. 

It is a requirement of all attendees that you help uphold our commitment to non-violence and de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values. 

Here are some suggestions to keep this a peaceful, civil protest: 

• Keep away from the Tesla employees, dealership, and their immediate surrounding property. Protest events at Tesla locations or other Musk properties should be focused on Elon Musk's role as a political actor and government agent. Protests should not be aimed at attacking the business interests of Tesla or their customers. 
• Stay on the sidewalk next to the public streets and keep off the lawn next to their building. 
• Stare past any agitators like they don’t exist. 
• Start a conversation about something random with someone near you. 
• Focus on music and the people driving by cheering in support. 

For your safety and the safety of those around you, consider not engaging with anyone that tries to provoke you. 

Parking and What to Bring:

• There is plenty of parking at the mall and near the Starbucks across the street from the Tesla Dealership.
• Bring a sign that expresses your feelings/what you're there for. 
• Water to stay hydrated, a sweater/coat, sunscreen, a hat, masks if you feel it necessary.
• Something to sit on if you want to attend, but cannot stand for hours on end.
• A playlist with upbeat music and a bluetooth speaker to help keep people around you positive and motivated.

“Courage is not the absence of fear, but rather the assessment that something else is more important than fear.” – Franklin D. Roosevelt 

Resist. Dissent. Persist.

title: Protest at Gabe Evans' Northglenn Office
description:
We are gathering peacefully at Gabe Evans' Northglenn Office every Friday at 11am to urge him to have the courage to speak with us, his constituents. We plead with him to defend our Constitution and our Democracy. We voice our concerns about our government's words and actions that look more like a dictatorship with each passing day.  We protest while we still can.

Rules (as stated by the police):

1. Please stay on the sidewalks only and do not block the sidewalks.  Standing in a single file at the front of the sidewalk or the back of the sidewalk is ideal.

2. No parking in the parking lot of the building where Gabe Evans' office is located. You can park in the lot across the street (at least for now).

3.No protest is permitted in the building (including no signs). There is a medical office in the building and there is a law that no protest can be within 100 feet of a medical facility.

Note: The church next door is very supportive and they welcome food donations for their food pantry!

Jonathan Goldsmith “The Most Interesting Man in the World”

We stand along the street in front of the North Church, the Brick Church off of Market Square in Portsmouth!

We call the event Civil Rights Sundays, we started in November of 2016 after Trump won the first time, and we were in the square every Sunday until Covid shut us down, then we went back out when Ukraine was invaded and brought back the name Civil Rights Sundays when Roe Vs Wade was overturned.

Please join us at 4 PM!


Call for a continued ceasefire in Gaza and for an end to our administration using our tax dollars to support a holocaust!

Donald and the un-elected Elon are trying to dismantle everything good about our government.  Say NO!


Ten protest sign messages or Meme messages, 
 
"Democracy Dies in Silence—Speak Out, Organize, Resist!"
"No Fascism in Our Future—Vote, Protest, and Protect Our Rights!"
"Fascism Thrives on Fear—We Rise with Courage!"

"Dismantle Hate, Defend Democracy, Demand Justice!"

Take a stand to defend our democracy! 

 Join us this Sunday!

title: Stop Elon Musk!
description:
Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership!

Unelected billionaire Elon Musk is stealing our money, our data, and our democracy. He's making decisions about our government behind closed doors, just to funnel money into his own hands. Let's stand united to say 'No Oligarchs!'

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood - not in business parking lots. For those who don't want to hunt for a parking spot, you can take the Green Vine bus from the transit center at the Vancouver Mall. It runs every 15 minutes and it's $1.25 each way. This line stops at Andresen Rd along Fourth Plain. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change.Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will call law enforcement if needed to shut down such unauthorized activity.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.

title: Defend Democracy — Chippewa Falls

Take action now to Defend Democracy! Take a stand against Trump, this administration, and DOGE for their unlawful and unconstitutional actions. Take a stand for protecting Social Security, Medicaid, federal agencies, national parks, due process, rule of law, the environment, and more. Defend our democracy for our families, friends, and neighbors. Get your signs ready and come let the community know this matters to you!

There's no such thing as bad weather, just bad clothing choices! Dress for Rally Success! Let's gather together and speak up for our children, grandchildren, and our community!

Two public parking lots on Bridge and River.

title: Take Down Tessla
description:
Elon Musk is destroying our democracy, and he's using the fortune he built at Tesla to do it. We are taking action at Tesla to stop Musk's illegal coup.

⚡Sell your Teslas, dump your stock, join the picket lines.

⚡ We're tanking Tesla's stock price to stop Musk.

⚡Stopping Musk will help save lives and protect our democracy.

The stakes couldn’t be higher. No one is coming to save us. Not politicians, not the media, not the courts.

Tesla Takedown is a peaceful protest movement. We oppose violence, vandalism and destruction of property. This protest is a lawful exercise of our First Amendment right to peaceful assembly.

Please park along Constitution Ave and walk to the traffic light at the shopping center entrance on Route 1 (a 2 minute walk). The shopping center is private property and we are NOT allowed to park there for protests. Please do not block the bus stop, the fire hydrants or any driveways. Thank you!


#TeslaTakedown #BoycottTesla

title: I91 Overpass Visibility Standout - Longmeadow

location.venue: Bark Haul Road (at the I91 overpass)

description:
How to Get There The address Bark Haul Road will get you there if you're using Waze. (Bark Haul Road is off Route 5.) The event is on the I-91 overpass. There's plenty of parking, although you can't park on the overpass.

If You Bring a Sign, Banner, or Flag For sign and banner lettering, bigger is better, so it can be easily read from the roadway. Flags are great, too. Wouldn't it be amazing to reclaim our flag? Mass DOT does not like things attached to the fence. They may visit, so be prepared to not have anything attached. Never drape anything over the fence, even with ropes, because it would be very dangerous if it accidentally fell onto the highway. Other Logistics No Port-A-Potties are available. Please take everything you brought away with you and leave the site totally clean. About These Standouts

Come join like-minded folks to demand that Trump, Musk, and the Republican-led Congress stop their unconstitutional power grab and the cruel destruction of our federal government.

We will hold banners, signs, and flags, and we'll wave to passing motorists. Many will beep and wave back at us, which feels nice! We'll show people that they're not alone and help give them the courage to join us and take a stand.

Please come out whether or not you have a sign or banner or flag. More people is better!

Come when you can, and leave when you must. You needn't be present for the entire 1 hour and 15 minute standout.

We may see a counter protester. If so, the best thing to do is just ignore them and spend our time and energy waving to motorists. Let's keep things 100% non-confrontational and non-violent, in words and body language. 

We welcome your energy and ideas, and we're looking forward to meeting everyone. Let's have some fun and make some good trouble

title: March for Integrity
description:
**PLEASE REGISTER VIA OUR WEBSITE AT [moneyoutofpolitics.org/join](https://moneyoutofpolitics.org/join)**

The [Money Out of Politics Movement](https://moneyoutofpolitics.org/) is organizing a peaceful, non-partisan march in **Washington, D.C.**, and at **all 50 state capitals**, where we expect to mobilize at least **two million Americans** to demand:

1. A Ban on Lobbyist Gifts: Prohibiting all direct or indirect financial incentives from lobbyists to members of Congress.
2. The End of Congressional Stock Trading: Preventing elected officials from using privileged information to personally benefit.
3. The Overturning of Citizens United: Eliminating unlimited corporate campaign contributions and restoring limits on political spending.
4. A Constitutional Amendment to Keep Money Out of Politics: Ensuring that future generations do not face the same corruption and undue influence in government.

These reforms are not partisan; they are essential to ensuring a government that serves the people rather than powerful special interests.

title: HUSKY for Immigrants - Community Visibility Days!
description:
**CT Must Defend And Extend HUSKY Coverage For Immigrants!** 

Join us for any of our upcoming “Community Visibility Days” at the Capitol Building and urge our legislators to stand on the right side of history. During those days, we’re inviting supporters, allies, and personally impacted individuals to join us at the Capitol Building to talk with legislators about why they MUST prioritize health equity and NOT put politics over the health of our community. 

What are we demanding from CT elected officials?

- Protect our progress and maintain HUSKY Medicaid coverage for children age 15 and under, and pregnant individuals. 

- Raise the age for HUSKY eligibility for immigrants up to age 26.

- Pass a strengethed TRUST Act to protect the personal data of immigrant community members who trusted the state of CT with their personal information when applying for HUSKY medicaid

*Never been to the Capitol before or spoken with legislators?* No worries! We’ll provide you with all the materials you need and do a quick training. Plus, we’ll have HUSKY Coalition leaders present to guide all attendees!

*Not available for the whole time?* Stop by anytime during the shifts to the left! Sign up and we will send you information

**Connecticut MUST continue our progress this year and ensure that all undocumented minors can access the care to set them up for healthy lives.**

title: Finding Kean Fridays
description:
NEW LOCATION - PLEASE READ
Join fellow NJ - 07 constituents for a weekly gathering as we work to #FindKean. Constituents are visiting his office every Friday. Let’s keep that momentum going.

Since Junior abruptly left his office in Bernardsville, we've tracked him down to his new digs at 100 Corporate Drive, Lebanon, NJ 08833.

We will continue to meet at 100 Corporate Drive, Lebanon, NJ every Friday. 

We will gather in the parking lot and small groups (2 per visit) can go into his office to meet with staff. We'll provide suggested talking points based on the votes and events of the past week. There is also an area near Rt. 22 where we can rally, but please note that if you have mobility issues, you may want to skip the rally portion. Otherwise, the building is easily accessed by anyone, and there is plenty of parking.

For those who will rally, please note the following:
-- There is just a grassy hill between people and traffic. 
-- Prepare for the weather - rain gear, boots, tick spray, sunscreen
-- We don't anticipate trouble, but we don't yet know what police presence there may be, so remember that this is a peaceful rally and we should not engage if there are counter protesters.

Whether you speak from the heart or bring hard-hitting facts, you deserve a hearing from your elected official. But be respectful of the staff’s time, and that of your fellow constituents who are waiting. Many Fridayers find it helpful to focus on one or two current issues.

· If you are addressing a Congressman’s vote or challenging his position on the issues, a personal story makes a difference.
· Leave a letter at the end of your visit if you like; the staff must log and respond to all letters.
 A thank-you and a polite tone at all times are a must.

Come for five minutes or stay for an hour. The more of us who show up each Friday, the better.

description:
Join us to rally in support of democracy and against the coup engineered by Musk and Trump! Bring a sign and a friend!

We practice peaceful non-violence and non-confrontation. Although we are all very concerned about Elon Musk' s activities and unconstitutional meddling in our democracy, we protest peacefully and with comradery among those who support refiusing to go along with Trump and Musk.

### So, if you encounter cybertrucks or hecklers, DO NOT RESPOND! We do not heckle those who have opposing views.

Marshals are present to protect us all and will assist. Columbus Dialogue Police will help de-escalate any confrontation. This has been an amazing group of demonstrators. Let's build friendships!
